title: Acrylic Circle template for bleaching t-shirts, t-shirt bleaching template, acrylic stencil, bleaching template, Sublimation Stencil, Circle
description:
Clear Acrylic Bleaching Stencil for Shirts. Stencil will come masked for protection during shipping.

Our acrylic stencils reduce bleach bleeding and overspray and provide you with a more desirable design.

When your stencil arrives please check your stencil for damage PRIOR to removing masking. If your stencil is damaged you must contact me with photos of the damaged stencil and packaging in order to receive a replacement. If you remove the masking then any damage is not covered.

Remove paper masking from Stencil Prior to use. Masking may be easily removed by gently peeling a corner. If Masking doesn't come off easy, please soak in water for about 5 mins then peel again.

***Square Template sizes*** 

Small- 8 x 8 inches. This Template will cover up to L shirt and smaller.
Medium- 10 x 10. This Template will cover up to XL shirt and smaller.
Large- 12 x 12 inches. This Template will cover up to 3X shirt and smaller.

***Wash With Water Only***

title: Dusty Blue Calligraphy Trifold Wedding Invitation, Simple Wedding Invitation, Order of the Day Timeline, Concertina Wedding Invitation
description:
Introducing our ever so versatile Trifold/Concertina Wedding Invitations, featuring a customisable timeline, a details panel, a main invitation panel, a cover and an RSVP that your guests can cut out and return.

⚫ HOW TO ORDER 

1. Choose how many invitations you would like and purchase.

2. Once your order has come through, we will then send you a message with an invitation form containing icon choices for the timeline and wording help.

3. When we have received your wording, we'll send you a digital file showing how your invitations will look with your details on within 1-2 business days (don't worry if you need tweaks, we're happy to do these for you!).

4. Once you're completely happy, we'll get these printed for you and posted out via a tracked courier.

⚫ ORDER OF THE DAY TIMELINE

Choose from over 50 different wedding related icons to fully personalise your Order of the Day Timeline.


⚫ RSVP

Your guests can cut out the RSVP panel (which will already have your return address printed on the reverse) that features names, accept/decline, dietary requirements, song choices, menu choices or more - it’s completely customisable to you.

⚫ COLOUR 

With some of our invitations we can change colours. If you would like a colour change, please send us a message and we can confirm this for you. As a rule of thumb, any design which only has text on can most likely change colour, whereas if the design features an illustration, it most likely can't change colour - but it's always worth an ask.

⚫ PDF CUSTOMER ADD ON

If you have placed an order with us and would like a digital copy, please also purchase the PDF Customer Add On. Please do not purchase this if you HAVEN'T ordered with us as we will have to refund your order and you will not receive anything.

⚫ PRINTING

Your stationery will be digitally printed on 250gsm luxury textured paper and include plain white envelopes for free.

⚫ SPECIFICATIONS

–  140mm x 140mm once folded, 420mm x 140mm when flat
– Plain white envelopes included free
– 250gsm luxury textured paper

⚫  EXTRAS

– Please enquire for wax seals for an additional price

⚫ PRODUCTION & DELIVERY

Your stationery will arrive with you in up to two weeks from design approval. Once posted, your stationery should arrive in the UK in 1-2 business days (this can be ever so slightly longer for Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland). We provide tracking information the moment it becomes available.

⚫ IMPORTANT DETAILS

– You can cancel an order once placed if we haven't already sent you either a digital file or physical item
– We cannot offer refunds if we have already sent you either a digital file or physical item as every item is personalised
– Colours may vary from those on screen due to every monitor having different colour settings
– As any colour is printed on, colours may vary slightly from sample to order and batches, similar to how wallpaper needs to be ordered in one batch for colour consistency

We can also amend the files for parties, anniversaries and much more.

Please note this is a DIGITAL item, which will be fully personalised at your request before being sent over in whichever format you require for you to print at home or via a printing company. If you would like a printed variation, please click 'ask a question' and send over a message with what you had in mind. We can then discuss all the fun things, like card types, colour options and quantities!

-------------------------
SPECIFICATIONS
-------------------------

Template sizes as standard are;

Invites & Menus: A5
RSVP & Save the dates: A6
Table Numbers: A5
Table Plan 40x50cm

COLOURS: The template comes as black ink on blank background as standard. As you can print yourself, you can choose whatever paper you like - we can offer suggestions if necessary. Font colour can be changed as you wish. If you have a colour scheme you are welcome to send over clear swatches via email for us to match up.

TEXT: You can change any and all wording across the listings, as well as the fonts if you have something different in mind.

----------------------------
HOW TO PURCHASE
----------------------------

First of all you must purchase the listings you require. You can add a note to seller at checkout or alternatively send us a message after purchase. If you have any questions, don't hesitate to drop us a message beforehand - we're happy to help in any way.

FULL personalisation information - outline which page you are referring to (if purchasing more than one design) and ALL wording requirements, in the format in which you wish your invite to be displayed. title: North Dakota Foodways, 8x10 Calligraphy Print
description:
Pork, lutefisk, hot dish, sugar beets...is your mouth watering yet?! Celebrate North Dakota's Foodways (the study of how food interacts with history and culture) with this original hand lettered print, flat printed right here in Alabama on cotton paper.

No matter where you call home, food is a sweet (and savory) reminder of the kinship, traditions, and region you share with others. Whether it's grits down South, chowder in the Northeast, or tacos out West, this nation's food culture is as diverse as the landscape and folks that call it home.

Here at Stately Made™, we believe in celebrating the traditions, culture, and history that make up who we are and where we call home in this great nation. Join in our Melting PotLuck collection, where we are highlighting the most iconic and traditional foodways in each state. Behind every dish is a story, a piece of history, and a reminder of home. So, next time you're at your grandma's house for supper or out at your favorite diner, eat, drink, and appreciate the story that goes beyond a few ingredients.

How do I use and clean the feather boas? 

After you receive the boas, please pull them out of the PVC bag(s), preferably outdoors, in order to get rid of debris formed during processing and shipping. The boas should be hung for 48 to 72 hours before use. The longer you hang them up, the better they will look. 

Feather boas are also washable. Clean the boas by hand washing in warm water and soap. Rinse off the soap with cold water. Then, wipe off the boas with a towel or paper towels. After removing most of the excess water, use a blow dryer to finish drying the boas and maintain their fluffiness. All of our feather products have been professionally cleaned, steamed, and sanitized. 

If the strings on the ends of the boa are too long, you may retie the string tightly as close as possible to the feathers and cut the rest off. The boa will not fall apart if you do this.

-FAQs-
Q: What is the production time?
A: Production time for note card sets and calling cards is generally 3-5 business days (M-F, excluding holidays). Production time for notepads is generally 3-7 business days (M-F, excluding holidays). Proofs for invitations are sent via Etsy messages within 1-3 business days (M-F, excluding holidays). Once proof approval is received, invitations are printed within three business days.

Q: What is the weight of paper stock that Lemon Grace uses for products?
A: Note cards, invitations, and calling cards are printed on professional grade, white, heavyweight 110lb. cover stock. 
Notepads are printed on professional grade, white 70lb. text weight paper.

Q: What kind of printing does Lemon Grace offer?
A: Note cards, calling cards, invitations, and notepads are digitally flat printed with premium archival inks.

Q: How do I add the personalization for my order?
A: Please enter all personalization information in the personalization box above the "add to cart" button.

Q: How are items packaged?
A: All stationery sets, invitations, and notepads are carefully packaged in resealable cello sleeves and are wrapped with a signature ribbon and tag. Perfect for gift-giving right out of the box! All calling card sets are packed in resealable cello sleeves.

Q: Will the colors on the screen look the same when printed?
A: Due to monitor settings, slight variances can occur with colors on screen versus printed on paper. The ink/envelope colors that match in title also match in printed color (i.e. turquoise ink matches the turquoise envelopes).

Q: Do you provide proofs before printing?
A: FOR INVITATIONS
Lemon Grace sends proofs for invitations only within 1-3 business days (M-F) of purchase. Invitations will not be printed without an approved proof.

FOR STATIONERY
Proofs or stationery are only sent with the purchase of the PROOF Add-On Listing. Production time may need to be extended if proofs are requested.

Q: What are your business hours?
A: Generally, our business hours are M-F, 9am-2pm. We are out of the studio on weekends and all federal holidays. Any other vacation times will be noted in the shop announcement at lemongrace.etsy.com.

title: Handwritten Watercolor Modern Calligraphy Place Cards // Folded Dinner Place Cards, Tented Wedding Table Cards, Event Seating Cards
description:
Set the mood for your big day with these bespoke watercolor place cards! Each of these gorgeous cards is cut, scored, and lettered by hand in a modern calligraphy style, making them beautifully unique and adding a personal touch to your guests' experience. 

This listing is for individual tented place cards that are entirely handmade, specifically for you. The modern calligraphy script is written in watercolor in any color you'd like, in a gorgeous brush-lettered style, making for a striking gradient effect!

These place cards add a personal touch to your special day through wedding favors, bridesmaids' gifts, wedding party gifts, bridal shower prizes, and more. They also make a great alternative to a classic seating chart, and give your guests a beautiful memento of your special day to take home with them!


P U R C H A S I N G · · · · · · · · · · · · ·

Please see the listing photos for a quick "how to order" rundown.

This listing is for place cards priced individually; however, I offer a discount for ordering 50 or more cards! Please message me BEFORE purchasing, and I'd be happy to set up a custom listing for you with the discount applied. This discount cannot be applied after ordering.

At checkout, you'll be able to select whether you'd like your cards to display first names or full names. If opting for first names only, I'm happy to add last initials at no extra cost; please clarify this when sending me your guest list. If desired, I can also add a table number at the bottom to turn them into escort cards/table cards for a small additional fee.


D E T A I L S · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · ·

• Size: 3.75 x 2.5 inches folded (3.75 x 5 inches unfolded)
• Ink: premium, professional-grade watercolors
• Paper: luxurious, lightly-textured watercolor paper

Your cards will be sent unfolded to ensure they stay beautiful during shipping, but are scored for your convenience.


O T H E R I N F O · · · · · · · · · · · · · · 

TURNAROUND TIME
Turnaround for this item varies by my seasonal workload, so please refer to the processing time for the current timeframe. If you're in a hurry, please message me BEFORE purchasing to discuss rush order options.

LETTERING
Please note that this writing style typically only uses lowercase letters by default. Please also keep in mind that since these are written by hand-- NOT typed-- there will be slight variations from letter to letter.

OTHER USES
In addition to weddings, these also make a great addition to any birthday, engagement party, bridal shower, bachelorette party, couple’s shower, rehearsal dinner, dinner party, baby shower, or any other event!

title: Ancient code of Chivalry - Latin English Wall Art 8.5" x 11" Scouts Honor
description:
Handlettered illustration of the Twelve Chivalric Virtues in English and Latin with Sword between the two lists. Sword is painted with a sheer golden Japanese ink (may be left plain upon request).

From Dr. George Grant on his blog, "Grantian Florilegium":

Sir Thomas Malory always seemed to give his readers more of a glimpse of his own age than of the age he was purportedly writing about. His tales were ostensibly about the daring-do exploits of King Arthur and his knights--but his times invariably showed through. And for good reason--he lived during the days when the Hundred Years War had finally shuddered to a conclusion and the Wars of the Roses had suddenly erupted. Like his mentor Geoffrey Chaucer, he was caught in the midst of this horrendous power struggle between the two great houses of the English royal line. And like Chaucer he served the Lancastrian line against the Yorkists. It was a time of anarchy, confusion, and widespread destruction.

Malory looked back longingly on the fading glory of chivalric feudalism. Beginning on this day in 1466, when he was imprisoned during one of the lawless scuffles that marked the Wars of the Roses, he determined to recall that time and those values in some permanent form. Le Mort d'Arthur was the result.

Not surprisingly, the ancient code of chivalry plays a prominent role in every aspect of the book--from character development to plot lines to conflict resolution. The code--formalized in the eleventh century by Bernard of Clairveuax--comprise twelve distinctive elements:

According to Bernard, a true Christian knight demonstrated chivalry first in integritas. He was to be trustworthy to all in his covenantal community. Second, a true Christian knight demonstrated chivalry in fidelitas. He was to be steadfastly loyal to all those with whom he was in relationship. Third, he demonstrated Christian chivalry in succurrere. He was to be helpful to any and all who might be in need. Fourth, he demonstrated benevolus. He was to be gracious and mannerly to everyone he met along the way. Fifth, he demonstrated urbanus. He was to be courteous upon every occasion. Sixth, he demonstrated benignus. He was to be selflessly kind. Seventh, he demonstrated referre. He was to obey all those that God had place in authority over him. Eighth, he deomonstrated hilaris. He was to be joyous and cheerful in the face of even the worst adversities. Ninth, he demonstrated frugalis. He was to be marked by an evident thrifty stewardship. Tenth, he demonstrated fortitudo. He was to be brave despite all the dangers that might cross his path. Eleventh, he demonstrated abulere. He was to be scrupulously clean in all his personal habits and hygiene. And finally, he demonstrated sanctus. He was to be piously reverent. Interestingly, the twentieth century British war hero, Robert Stephenson Baden-Powell, utilized Bernard’s code as the basis for the virtues to be inculcated in his Boy Scouts. But centuries before Lord Baden-Powell tapped the principles and elements of chivalry for his fledgling movement, Thomas Malory was building his tales of Arthurian romance around them.

There is perhaps no better guide to understanding the purpose and intent of Malory--and the times that he baptized upon the Arthurian legends--than this remarkable ethical code.

http://grantian.blogspot.com/2006/07/malorys-chivalry.html

title: West End I colorshift vegan handmade watercolor dot card
description:
This 8.5cm x 5.5cm (3.34 x 2.1 in) dot card includes samples of Reneeissance Colours’ West End I collection of handmade watercolour paint on 315g cardstock. You will receive:

1.	Phoenix: pink to orange to yellow
2.	Lyceum: orange to yellow to green
3.	Fortune: gold to green 
4.	Trafalgar: tan to green to blue
5.	Dominion: green to red
6.	Novello: green to blue to purple
7.	Sondheim: blue to purple
8.	Lyric: purple to green

Because of the nature of handmade watercolors, some of the dots may be smaller or larger than pictured. 

The West End I collection of paints are all named after theatres in London’s West End. The pigment used to make this collection has a slightly larger particle size, which means the paint appears sparkly, but requires less water and must be applied thickly to achieve an opaque appearance. West End I colours shift best on black paper. They will show up on white paper, but the shift will not be as apparent. 

Our homemade binder is made with the highest quality gum arabic available. We do not use honey or any other animal products in our paints, so they are vegan-friendly.

Not intended for use on skin. Please do not ingest.

For best results, apply a drop of water to the paint and wait a minute, then reactivate the paint with a paint brush.

For tips on how to use dot cards, check out our Youtube video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LhtYxCVETKY

To see approximately how much paint you can get from a dot, check out our other video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZPZRXTHt0UE


INTERNATIONAL SHIPPING NOTE: I am currently shipping from London, England. I offer affordable international shipping because I want to share my paint with everyone. However, the postal system has been slow and unpredictable lately, so your paints may take longer than usual to reach you. Once I post them, I have no control over how long they take to arrive. title: Beginner Level 1- Copperplate Calligraphy Worksheet Set: Includes Drills Worksheet, Alphabet Worksheet, Guidelines & Blank Practice Sheet
description:
*Updated and improved as of March 2020! 

This is the full set of Beginner Level 1 worksheets, which focuses on a traditional lowercase calligraphy alphabet and is the most basic level of worksheet offered. The Beginner Level 1- The Very Basics set includes an exercise for each letter of the alphabet, which includes letters for tracing and space for individual practice. 

 This listing ALSO includes an incredibly detailed page of letter stroke guidelines, which outline the exact process to construct each letter, and a blank sheet with guidelines for additional practice. 

The second worksheet set is for calligraphy drills, which we recommend starting with before venturing on to the alphabet worksheets. These worksheets are great because you can print and re-print them as many times as you'd like for unlimited practice. 

Upon purchasing this listing, you will receive the following: 
- One printable worksheet set containing seven pages in PDF form. Page one contains an overview of recommended materials, pages two through five contain lowercase alphabet practice, page six contains a page of stroke guidelines, and page seven is a blank page with guidelines for additional practice. 
- A second printable worksheet set containing the CalligraPhilly Drills worksheet. 

PLEASE NOTE: This listing does not include word practice or flourishing sheets, and does not contain an uppercase alphabet. It contains two documents, the first with materials recommendations, four pages of lowercase alphabet guides, one master stroke guideline sheet and a blank practice sheet, and the second with drills. Please read the description carefully, as there are no refunds for digital downloads.

title: Calligraphy Set For Beginners, Calligraphy Pen Set, Calligraphy Kit, Dip Pen Set, oblique pen holder, 19 Calligraphy Nibs, Wooden Pen Set
description:
Calligraphy dip pen set is made with love by our finest craftsmen. Fancy pen set is a perfect calligraphy pens set for beginners. Oblique calligraphy pen set has a wood dip pen, a wood oblique calligraphy dip pen, 19 calligraphy dip pen nibs set, 18ml dip pen black ink, oblique calligraphy pen holder and a beautiful gift box.

Caligraphy kit has two different caligraphy pens. Wooden pen kit has dip pens that are a straight nib black wooden caligraphy pen and a black wooden calligraphy oblique pen. Professional calligraphy set has a 18 ml fountain pen black ink well. Calligraphy pen for beginners comes with 19 different calligraphy nibs set for different writing styles. Caligraphy pen set also includes a golden calligraphy nib holder.

Calligraphy dip pen nib set is very high quality coligraphy pen kit. Coligraphy set are designed for a comfortable grip and has high quality manuscript pen holder. Pen nib holder is made of high quality wood. Calligraphy nib set has calligraphy pen nibs that hold a lot of ink to ensure a smooth clog free writing. Oblique dip pen provides a great writing experience.

Calligraphy pen oblique and calligraphy pen professional is a perfect gift for men and women. Caligraphy pens and ink set comes in a exquisite black box with golden writing and beautiful calligraphy ink holder. Calligraphy pen nib and calligraphy holder provide a perfect dip pen calligraphy experience. High quality calligraphy pens, ink well, dip nib, calligraphy nibs and holders make it a complete gift which everyone would cherish for life.

Our calligraphy kit comes with 100% customer satisfaction. We guarantee, you will love this wooden pen calligraphy set as this is a perfect calligraphy kit for beginners as well as calligraphy pen professionals. Combination of oblique dip pen and straight nib pen is perfect for everyone.


Our calligraphy nibs come with protective oils on them to ensure they reach you in the best condition possible. Please follow the instructions below before using the nibs. 

Instructions 
1. Please remove the nib already installed in the pen by gently pulling it out. 
2. Dip a soft toothbrush in water to moisten it. 
3. Squeeze a little bit of toothpaste/dish detergent onto the brush. 
4. Scrub the brush on nib for about 30 seconds. 
5. Once finished scrubbing, drop the nib in water for a few seconds to get the toothpaste/dish detergent off. 
6. Fish the nib out of the water and wipe it dry with cloth or paper towel. 
7. Push the nib in the pen, dip it in the ink about half way through and enjoy a magnificent writing with your new calligraphy pen! 
8. After use, please wipe the nib clean so it works great in the next use as well.

Support: Please, before contacting me for support, read the pdf files. If you still need help, contact me and i will do my best to help you.

*****

*****

❤ Please, visit my main shop to download more fonts: https://www.etsy.com/ca/shop/CreativeStudioNY

*****

INSTRUCTIONS:

HOW TO INSTALL THE FONT ON PC OR MAC:

Unzip your font folder and double click on the font to install it.

*For Ipad and iPhone users, you can search on the "app store" some free "font manager" app, it is 100% compatible on IPad and iPhone as well.


///


CRICUT AND SILHOUETTE:

Please note. I do not offer support for Cricut, however, I provide you with some instructions bellow that might help you.

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON PC:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF). Double-click it!
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.
Congratulations! Your font is now installed.
Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON MAC OS X:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF).
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.

Congratulations! Your font is now installed.

Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE IN IOS 11 OR HIGHER ON AN IPAD OR IPHONE:

First, go to the app store and get a free app called iFont. Once you’re in the app store, click on the Search button down at the bottom and type in iFont. Click on the download icon. After the app finishes downloading, click to open iFont.

Download the font to your iPad or iPhone.

iFont should open with the Open Zip Archive screen. You should then be directed back to iFont. On the left, you’ll see an option to Install the Maker Penwriting Regular font. Tap the Install button. You’ll be guided through a series of menus. Tap Allow. Settings should open showing a window to Install Profile. Tap Install. You may be prompted for your device’s passcode. You may have to tap install a couple more times to complete the process. You should see a screen that says Profile Installed. Tap Done. The font is now installed on your device.

Restart the Cricut Design Space app. Click on the text at the bottom. Click on the All tab because of the app defaults to the Cricut tab. Type in the name of the font you just installed. Tap on it. You should now be back at the Canvas screen. Type in text to see what it looks like.


///


HOW TO MANUALLY INSTALL FONTS FOR SILHOUETTE:


Note: You do not need to download the font into the Silhouette software. Once the Mia font is installed on your computer in your font directory, the font will show up as an available option for cutting letters once the Silhouette software is opened.


INSTALL THE FONT ON A PC:

1. After you purchase the font, your font will be available to download. Right-click on the font link from Etsy and "Save link as" to your computer. A zipped folder will be downloaded to your default download location on your computer. It will be named "Mia Font Commercial.zip" on your PC:

Depending on your download environment, the download may show in the downloads section of your browser OR in the default download location

Open the downloaded folder

2. Double-click on "Mia Font Commercial.zip" folder to install (A font management window will open)

3. Select the Install option in the upper-left of the window

4. The Install button will turn grey, indicating that the font has been installed


INSTALL THE FONT ON A MAC:

1. After you purchase the font, a zipped folder will be available and downloaded to your default download location on your computer. It will be named "Mia Font Commercial.zip" on your PC:

Depending on your download environment, the download may show in the downloads section of your browser OR in the default download location

Open the downloaded folder

2. Double-click on "Mia Font Commercial.zip" folder to install (A font management window will open)

3. Select the Install option in the lower-right of the window

4. The font management window will close, indicating that the font has been installed

Voila! :)

title: Watercolor brush "Golden 2" - Vegan Cruelty Free Softer Synthetic Squirrel by Maria Raczynska
description:
Maria Raczynska “Golden 2” brushes. 
Round 8 and flat 3/4 - the finest quality soft squirrel synthetic fiber brushes. 

"Golden 2" is a very high end line because of a special synthetic fibers specifically created for these brushes. Real-squirrel hair brushes are very soft, often too soft. These are made to mimic real squirrel hair, but the hair isn't too soft, and it's springy at the same time, something real squirrel brushes often lack on.

These brushes are designed in California, by a professional artist Maria Raczynska with help from one of the best brush makers in England.

title: Name Stickers for Bridesmaid Proposal, Champagne Flute, Caligraphy Vinyl decals, personalised custom gift box stickers
description:
Perfect for personalising your own glassware, gift boxes, gift bags or other items.

Our decals will stick to any smooth surface - glass, metal, wooden, plastic, paper or card products. 

Full instructions are provided in EVERY order with links to our helpful videos.

If you have any questions, read through the information below and if you can't find an answer please do ask for help.

Please remember:
***To order your names,  add to the personalisation box or put a list of names in the "Note to Seller" box at the checkout***
AND make sure the quantity box (which may be shown at the checkout) is updated to reflect the number of names you need.


A full range of professional-grade vinyl colours is available to choose from.

We can cut larger stickers on our machines, so please get in touch if you require a longer customised item.

═════════════════════════════════

To help you find the information you require quickly, look at the index below and then and scroll down to the relevant section.

Section 1 -  Size Ordering Guide
Section 2 - How To Order
Section 3 - Vinyl Info (material, colours, design)
Section 4 - Post Payment
Section 5 - Shipping
Section 6 - Returns

═════════════════════════════════


1 - SIZE ORDERING GUIDE
=========================

Sticker Width
-------------------
This is the size you would like your decal to be.  
Please note this listing is for names primarily - we cannot make wedding roles eg Mother of the Bride, Bridesmaid at a size smaller than 9cm/3.5inch, and they may be made over 2 lines at this size.
If in doubt, please enquire prior to ordering, and tell us what you intend to place them on.


Sticker Height
--------------------

The height of the sticker(s) will be based on the width of the name(s)/word(s) AND the number of names/words provided.

For example, if you just want ONE sticker that says "Jo" at 4 inches wide that will have a width of 4 inches and the height will be scaled accordingly.

If you want 3 names (e.g. Jo, Hannah, Charlotte) and want them 4 inches wide.

Charlotte, being the longest word, will be sized to 4 inches wide and the height of Charlotte will be used to determine the height of the stickers for Jo & Hannah. 

In this case, the width of Jo & Hannah will be LESS than 4 inches.

If you are submitting multiple words or names for the same sticker width the height will be based on the longest word you have submitted.



═════════════════════════════════

2 - HOW TO ORDER
==================

Carefully read the following:

To place your order:

1 - Determine the size of the sticker you require 

2 - Now select the width of sticker you require from the pull-down "Sticker Width" menu

3 - Select the colour of your sticker from the colour pull-down menu

4 - Telling us what you want on your stickers

In the Personalisation, box enter the names/words you require.

If you need more than one sticker, ensure you put "S1-, S2-, S3- etc" in front of the words

Examples: 

Peter requires 3 individual names. Fredrick, Alison, Peter

So he would enter: S1- Fredrick S2- Alison S3- Peter

Yasmin wants "Self Raising Flour" and needs it on two lines, so that is 2 stickers

So she would enter: S1- Self Raising S2- Flour


5 -  Change the quantity box to the correct number you need (taking into account if you require multiple lines - remember 1 line = 1 sticker). 

On a mobile device the quantity option may not appear until you have added the item to your cart, so remember the number of stickers you require


6 - Then click on Add to Cart/Basket and proceed to the checkout to complete shipping and billing details.


═════════════════════════════════
3 - DECAL INFORMATION

• A high-quality grade decal for you to apply to your OWN boxes or bags, or other smooth surfaces (plastic, glass, wood, metal)

• Precision cut on a commercial industrial machine to ensure a clean crisp outline

• Clear release paper is provided, so you can see exactly where you are placing it on the item

• Waterproof - if applying to items that require washing, wash by hand, not in a dishwasher

═════════════════════════════════

4 - POST PAYMENT

VERY IMPORTANT POINTS:

• You will receive email confirmations once you have placed and paid for your order. 

• **DOUBLE CHECK* everything in the email confirmation is correct. (Especially your email address and the delivery address, as sometimes if you have recently moved the details are not updated.)

• We cannot be held liable for incorrect postal details and can only ship to the address provided at the time of ordering. 

• Please contact us immediately if you notice an error, and we will work with you to fix this - sometimes we are able to turn items around very quickly, so do get in touch as soon as you notice.

• Do keep an eye on your Etsy account/email inbox after you have placed your order in case we need to contact you concerning your order 

• After we dispatch your order you should also receive an email.


═════════════════════════════════

5 - SHIPPING

Shipping details are shown at the checkout stage.

If delivery is outside of the UK, please remember standard shipping IS NOT tracked. So if you want to track your order, please upgrade to the tracked option.


═════════════════════════════════

5 - RETURNS

Personalised stickers cannot be returned for a refund

title: Destination Wedding Invitation Passport Invitation Tropical Invitation Set Beach Wedding in Rose Gold and Blush Watercolor by Luckyladypaper
description:
Destination Wedding Invitation - Passport Invitation - Tropical Invitation Set Beach Wedding in Rose Gold and Blush Watercolor by Luckyladypaper - Hard Copy Generic Sample set -OR- Deposit towards customizing your very own invitations! - PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING DETAILS CAREFULLY BEFORE PURCHASING THIS LISTING.

♥ Oh Hi there Lucky Ladies and Lads in Love! 

When purchasing this listing, please select from the Purchase Options dropdown menu to either select the Hard Copy Sample set or Customized Deposit.  

♥ If you select the HARD COPY SAMPLE OPTION, you are purchasing a set of hard copy generic samples of the Passport Invitation Suite shown in the photos printed on each of the different paper choices, along with all of the different envelope choices so you can see and feel the different options in person before you customize your very own invitation set.  

      • Once you purchase the Hard Copy Sample option, your samples will be mailed to you in 1-2 business days via first class USPS mail and you should receive them in 3-6 business days from the date they are mailed. 

♥ If you select the CUSTOMIZED DEPOSIT OPTION, you are purchasing a deposit towards your full customized Passport Invitation order to get the design process started.  Customization of the text and colors of this design are included in your Customized Deposit purchase. 

****************************************************

♥ INSTRUCTIONS FOR CUSTOMIZED DEPOSIT OPTION:

Please scroll through all of the photos in the listing to find the options and pricing is on the last photo. To start your order, purchase the Customized Deposit option from the dropdown menu and then send this shop a message with the answers to the following 14 questions (please copy and paste into your reply and add your responses).
 
1. Have you read the HOW IT WORKS and TURNAROUND TIMES section below? Please review and confirm your understanding of our process and timeline. 

2. What is the exact wording you would like on your invitation card? IMPORTANT: please define which wording goes on each page and PLEASE DO NOT TYPE IN ALL CAPS
- You may pick to have just the 2 pages printed on the inside of the passport cover (traditional invitation wording page and the passport photo page) or you can purchase an insert a sheet which gives you 4 extra pages (plus the 2 pages that are printed on the back side of the cover to equal total 6 pages inside the passport) to include things like information about the accommodations, itinerary, other events and the location). 
-IMPORTANT: Please be sure to triple check your wording for spelling and accuracy before you send it to me as revisions after I create your initial proofs will cause delays.  
-You may use the example text here, if needed: https://www.dropbox.com/s/xbt5itz30llj9ey/Passport%20Sample%20Wording%20Lucky%20Lady%20Paper.pdf?dl=0
 
3. Exact wording you would like on your RSVP card (if purchasing RSVP cards) and whether you prefer the 
a) Card with envelope (either traditional or boarding pass style) or 
b) Postcard style.  If purchasing the postcard style, please include the return address you would like printed on the card.

4. If ordering RSVP cards with envelopes, would you like your return address printed on the front of the envelopes ($0.75 each envelope)?
 
5. What are your Color choice(s) if different from the rose gold and blush colors in the sample photo? 
 
6. What is the exact # of sets you would like printed? TIP: order 5-10 extra in case you need to invite more people/need to resend invites because some you sent got lost in the mail and for your own keepsakes because if you need to order a few extra later, the price per invite for orders less than 25 is higher). 
 
7. Would you like REAL foil (shiny/metallic) finishing on the front cover? If you do not select this option, I will apply a faux foil effect on the graphics and text so that it has the appearance of real foil but won't actually be shiny/metallic. If you would like real foil, the only paper choice available is Luxe Petal.  Foil colors available are rose gold, regular gold and silver.
 
8. What is your printing paper choice? Note: see below for paper choice descriptions. If you are unsure after reading the descriptions, please purchase the Hard Copy Sample purchase option first so that you can see and feel the different options in person first.
a) Luxe Petal with REAL foil on the front cover of the passport
b) Matte Satin with REAL foil on the front cover of the passport
c) Stardream Shimmer (not available if you answered "yes" to question 6)
d) Plain Jane (not available if you answered "yes" to question 6)
 
9. What is your free matching Envelope Choice (White or Kraft Paper)? White shimmer envelopes are available for an extra $0.11 per envelope.  Also please note if you require any additional envelopes and how many. 
 
10. Would you like to purchase the matching envelope liners? You can view our selection here: https://www.etsy.com/shop/luckyladypaper?section_id=21388638
   - If yes, please specify which design and the quantity you would like to purchase.
 
11. Would you like to add addressing service for your envelopes?  
   - If yes, please specify what type(s) of addressing service(s) would you like from the following options:
a) Just return address on the invitation envelopes and/or RSVP envelopes ($0.75 each envelope)
b) Both Guest address and return address on the invitation envelopes ($1.50 each envelope)
c) Just Guest address on the invitation envelopes ($1.00 each envelope)

12. Would you would like to purchase any other products to match this design such as save the dates, menus, programs, place cards, table numbers, seating charts, guestbook posters, favor tags, banners/signs, thank you cards, etc? If yes, please note if they will be ordered at a later date or if you would like to include them in this same order to have them shipped together. 

13. How did you find your way to this shop? 

14. Please attach a bright, high resolution photo for the passport page. It will need to attached to a message (it cannot be included in "order notes").

****************************************************

♥ HOW IT WORKS and TURNAROUND TIMES FOR CUSTOMIZED DEPOSIT OPTION:

Without any revisions, the process outlined below takes roughly 3.5 calendar weeks (including shipping). We recommend starting your order at least 4 weeks before you would like to have your order in hand in case revisions are needed. Please read details below carefully. 

DETAILS:

After you purchase the Customized Deposit option and send me your answers to the questions above, I work one on one with you until your design is perfect for you. Your first PDF proofs will be emailed to you within 3 business days, and you may use 3 free revisions if needed. Revisions will be completed within 1-2 business days of request. When you are ecstatic with your design and give me the OK, I will set up a second listing for you to pay the balance due to print your order. The deposit you already paid will go towards the price of your full order.  After you pay the balance in full, your cards will go to print and will ship within 8-12 business days (shipping typically takes 2-3 business days) within the USA!

ORDERS PLACED OVER THE WEEKEND:

Complete orders (deposit + complete questionnaire received) placed on Saturday will receive PDF design proofs on Wednesday. Complete orders placed on Sunday will receive PDF design proofs on Thursday.

HOURS OF OPERATION:
I operate Monday – Friday 10am – 6pm CT.  CLOSED Saturday and Sunday.

Thanks so much again! I look forward to traveling along side you on your invitation journey :)
-Aimee

ps- follow luckyladypaper at www.instagram.com/luckyladypaper and/or facebook for special promotions and more photos of our products! 

****************************************************

♥ PAPER CHOICE DESCRIPTIONS for the Passport Covers: Note: It is best to see the paper choices in person before placing your full order. To order samples of all of the different paper choices first, please select the Hard Copy Sample purchase option. 

Our wedding invitations are flat printed on the highest quality heavy card stock using a commercial press, resulting in the most beautiful, professional quality wedding invitations.  We use only the absolute best in printing and paper, giving our stationery a level of quality that is unmatched.

You have the following options for your Passport Cover:
 
• LUXE PETAL is a heavy card stock with a luxurious, rose petal soft matte coating on the outside and a smooth uncoated finish on the inside. Our most realistic choice when compared to a real passport!

• MATTE SATIN is a heavy card stock with a regular smooth matte coating on the outside and inside.

• STARDREAM SHIMMER is a pearlescent, slightly shimmery heavy card stock. Since it is opalescent and actually sparkles, it reminds me of how the sand and ocean sparkle in the sun!

• PLAIN JANE is a smooth (untextured) heavy card stock without coating.

****************************************************

♥ PLEASE NOTE THE FOLLOWING BEFORE PURCHASING THIS LISTING

• All prices listed in these item details are in USD. 

• The fonts shown in the design for this listing are part of the design.  Requests to change the font will be considered for a $25 extra design fee if approved.

• Hard Copy Samples can not be customized to your wording and/or colors. If you would like to receive a hard copy sample of your customized design, you may elect to receive your hard copy sample(s) prior to your full order being printed, after purchasing your customized invitation set.

You can bind them by either putting two staples down the center of the spine or secure with ribbon/twine which you can purchase at any craft supply. Personally, I find the ribbon/twine method to be easiest and also more attractive than using staples. Please see the quick tutorial video here: https://www.instagram.com/p/BVslS8XgoNb/?taken-by=luckyladypaper

• Envelope liners come unassembled and unbound to the envelopes. You must assemble them by applying a thin line of glue stick to the top of the liner and sliding them into the envelope. Please see the quick tutorial video here: https://www.instagram.com/p/BVshigZg-Jr/?taken-by=luckyladypaper

♥ FAQS

Q: What is the price per invitation?
A: The pricing depends on your quantity, paper choice, and which options you choose to include in your invitation suite. Please scroll through all of the photos in this listing for options and pricing.

title: Timeless, Elegant Calligraphy Wedding Invitations | Traditional Script Printed Wedding Invitation Suite | Kamryn
description:
This classic and traditional wedding invitation will perfect for your sophisticated wedding with an abundance of elegant calligraphy.  Your invitation suite is ready to be customized and  printed on modern extra thick card stock for a wedding invite  your guests will remember. If the script is too much for you, just let me know and we can take some out! This design is yours to personalize any way you'd like.

I'll take care of the printing and worry about those details so you get the best paper, nothing flimsy!

This set is modern and traditional, and will be sure to impress your guests with it's classic beauty.

✨WHY THESE ARE RIGHT FOR YOU ✨
When I got married, I was frustrated. I flipped through book after book and nothing was quite right. A lot were almost right and all I wanted to do is combine a few designs together to create something perfect. That's what I strive to do with each and every wedding that I work with. If you want to merge design elements from 2 suites together, great! If you want to add in a colored envelope or a wax seal or a vellum wrap - we can do that! You're working one on one with a designer that can change those things to make these uniquely you. I don't have a limit to the number of revisions you get, that's not how I want to run my business. We'll make it perfect.

✨EXTRAS THAT ARE ALWAYS INCLUDED ✨
- unlimited rounds of proofs
- paper swatches mailed out to you if you would like to see your options
- complimentary printed proofs (if time allows - they take about 2 weeks)
- your address printed on the RSVP envelope
- your return address printed on the mailing envelope

**printed guest addresses are an additional $0.75
✨WHAT MAKES THESE SPECIAL✨
My favorite part of the classic collection is the paper. I'm a bit of a paper snob and I've tried all the papers. I have these printed a crisp, 120# Mohawk Superfine cardstock in either white or ivory, OR you can upgrade the invites to a double thick 240# weight for extra luxurious design.

Double thick cardstock is quite literally - twice the thickness. These invitations are printed on 240 lb cardstock with an eggshell texture. They feel luxurious in your hands and will make such a great impression to your guests. Its roughly the thickness of a paper coaster. 

You can see all of the designs in the double thick collection here - https://etsy.me/2zuLrjq

✨SAMPLES✨
Samples are always available and typically ship within 2-3 days. If I'm out of stock I'll contact you with an updated ship date. Samples will include the invite, info card, RSVP, belly band, envelope liner and samples of both single and double thick paper in white and ivory.

✔️HOW TO ORDER
1  • • • Payment

To begin an order, select your options from the dropdown menu. 

If you have any custom requests that you don't see from the dropdown menu, please send me a message with details so I can further advise you on any additional costs. 


2 • • • Provide Your Wording

In the personalization box, please provide the information required to create your proofs including:
• full invitation wording exactly as you'd like it on your invitation
• custom text for your info card (hotel reservations, booking information, reception information, shuttles, website, etc.)
• RSVP date
• any custom RSVP text requests
• food choices if applicable 
• RSVP address
• mailing envelope return address
• what color paper you would like to use (white or ivory)

OR

Fill out the form on my website - https://www.invitedbylamaworks.com/pages/client-wording-form

If you fill out the form, it will walk you through common questions and wording suggestions!

3 • • • Proof Approval

You will receive a custom proof of all of your pieces within 2 business days after purchase. (please note, I do take weekends off to be present with my family). Three rounds of revisions are included. Each additional revision is $35 per round.

Nothing is printed without your approval!

Your proofs will arrive via your Etsy account, so please either check into Etsy frequently or turn on your conversation email notifications. If I don't hear from you within 48 hours, I will also reach out through email. 

Proofs will be sent to you in a PDF formatted to print out at home on regular printer paper so you can see everything in real size. 

4 • • • Guest Addresses (optional)
If you have added guest address printing to your order, I will email you an Excel or Google Sheets (if requested) template required for your guest addresses. Please note that addresses must be provided in this template, I am not able to reformat them for you.

5 • • • Production & Arrival

Your custom printed designs typically ship within 7-10 days of proof approval. All orders ship Priority Mail (2-3 days) unless we have discussed other options.

✔️ADDITIONAL ADD ONS
Info Card (any size) - $1.65
Belly Band - $0.75
Solid Color Envelope Liner - $0.70
Printed Envelope Liners - $1.80
Menus - $1.65
Place Cards - $1.20
Wax Seals - $1.85
Seating Chart (digital file) - $125

*need something extra? Send me a message and we can put together a custom package for you!


FAQs:
✔️WILL I SEE PROOFS?
Absolutely! I don't print anything without your approval to do so.

You will receive your first round of proofs within 2 business days of submitting your order. If something comes up and there will be any delay I'll let you know. Please note, I do try to take weekends off to be present with my family.

✔️HOW LONG DOES IT TAKE?
Most orders can be ready to go in as little as 10-14 days. Please note that the full order time - from proofing to delivery - may vary based on the time it takes to proof your designs, which is entirely up to ou. The faster you are able to proof and approve your design to print, the sooner I can begin production.

✔️CAN I PERSONALIZE A SAMPLE?
I am not able to customize samples with your text in them. You will receive a sample invitation that is pictured in the listing along with paper samples in white and ivory, single and double thick.

✔️CAN I CHANGE THE WORDING?
Absolutely! You can use whatever wording makes your heart happy.

✔️CAN YOU RUSH MY ORDER?
You bet! Rush design, printing and processing is available for an additional $150. Please message me with the date you need them by for a custom listing.

SEE THE COLLECTION
To see all of the designs that are part of the Classic  collection - click here --> https://etsy.me/2QE8SMh


CANCELLATIONS & REFUNDS
I encourage you to message me with any questions or concerns you may have before purchasing a listing.

Orders cancelled within 1 business day of purchase will be fully refunded as long as I have not started working on your poofs.

Orders cancelled after receiving a custom proof, but before we go to print will receive a 50% refund.

Orders cancelled after the physical production process will not be refunded in any way.

Due to the personalized nature of all invitation refunds, replacement or exchanges are not possible once approval to print has been received. All packages are insured during shipping, so if there is any damage to your order, replacements will be provided as long as proof of the damage is provided for the insurance claim.

description:
Does your hand cramp up at the thought of writing your return address 100s of times?  Mine does!  These custom stamps will not only save you from the dreaded hand cramp, but they also add a beautiful touch to your envelopes!  I just love how a stamped return address looks on the back flap of an envelope.  

Now with more flexibility!  Choose from either a wood address stamp or a Trodat self-inking stamp, and pick your ink color as well.

If you're purchasing a wood stamp and you'd like more ink pad color options, additional colors and types of ink pads are available here: https://etsy.me/2MqDe5l

----------
TIMING
----------

I pride myself in providing quick and efficient service, and most customers have their stamps in hand within 5-7 business days after ordering (excludes Sat and Sun). Once I receive your order, you will receive a mock-up within 1-2 business days. After the mockup is approved for production, it takes 1-2 days for the stamp to ship. After that, it's up the post office to deliver to you in a timely manner.

At checkout, you can choose either first-class shipping, which typically takes 5-7 business days (although is sometimes faster!), or you can upgrade to priority mail which takes 2-3 business days depending on your location.  However, these delivery times are not guaranteed by the post office.Does your hand cramp up at the thought of writing your return address 100s of times?  Mine does!  These custom stamps will not only save you from the dreaded hand cramp, but they also add a beautiful touch to your envelopes!  I just love how a stamped return address looks on the back flap of an envelope.  

Now with more flexibility!  Choose from either a wood address stamp or a Trodat self-inking stamp, and pick your ink color as well.

If you're purchasing a wood stamp and you'd like more ink pad color options, additional colors and types of ink pads are available here: https://etsy.me/2MqDe5l

------------
DETAILS
------------

First, choose either a wood stamp or a self-inking stamp.  I personally love the wood stamps, because you can change ink colors at will!  Wood stamps arrive with handle installed.  You can also choose to add on a standard felt ink pad in blue, red, or black!

The self-inking stamps are the highly respected Trodat brand.  Choose from a variety of colorful inks, which will last for up to 10,000 impressions!  Note that you cannot easily change ink colors with self-inking stamps.

Next, enter the desired name and address exactly as you'd like it to appear on the stamp. I will contact you within 1-3 business days with a digital proof of your design.

Once you approve your proof, the stamp will be delivered to you in about 5-7 business days!

This stamp is roughly 1"x2.5", depending on your exact text. Stamp previews shows an accurate size on a 5×7″ envelope.

------------------------

The purpose of my shop, Fresh Cut Prints is to encourage, send joy, and show love to others through the written word and good old-fashioned snail mail.  As a society we've become so isolated from one another, but we can change that, one card at a time.  #intentionalloveproject

Please feel free to contact me with any questions, and visit me online at

title: Bridesmaid wedding party tote bag / maid of honor /matron of honor/ hand lettering/ wedding party gift/bridesmaid gift/ calligraphy/custom
description:
These tote bags are great for your bridal party! These bags come with either “bridesmaid”, “maid of honor”, “matron of honor”, “mother of the bride” , “mother of the groom”, and “flower girl” on one side only 

Names can be added for an additional $2.00 per name, per bag. 

Both sides of the bag can be printed for an additional $2.00 per side 

These bags are great for day of favors and great for extra shoes, clothes, etc. My bridesmaids loved them! 

Each bag has the text in black heat transfer vinyl. Must be spot cleaned but can be put in washer, wash cold, hang dry, and do not iron directly on the design. 

If you need more than 3, please message me to ensure you get your items on time, depending on how much I have in my queue. Other colors can be available for an additional price, just message me! 

These bags are not meant to be overstuffed and overweighed with items. I am not responsible if the strap breaks due to overstuffing the bag or weighing it down with extremely heavy items 

TO ORDER: message me with any questions about details! If you just want to order, place an order and if you want names, please leave the names in the message to seller. Please note that names/double sided will not be added if they are not paid for.
personalization_instructions: Please enter the title (bridesmaid, Maid of honor, flower girl, mother of the bride, etc) and a name if applicable!

title: My Fingers May Be Small But I Can Still Wrap My GRANDPA Around Them - Kids Printable Handprint Artwork
description:
This is a listing for a digital file that you can print and use at home! 

This file includes the words "My fingers may be small, but I can still wrap my grandpa around them". 

Please see my other listings for other names (daddy, papa, family, etc.) or let me know if you need another title :)

Print on card-stock and add your child's handprint! 

Makes a great frame-able gift! Great for nursery or preschool classroom art. 

You could also cut these letters out of heat transfer vinyl on your Cricut or Silhouette and apply on a tote bag, and put your child's handprint on it. Great gift for grandparents.

100% hand drawn lettering. 

The digital hand is NOT included in the file - ONLY the lettering. The digital hand is to show you how you can use the lettering with your own child's handprints :)

This SVG design can be 'ungrouped' :)

*******

THIS IS A DIGITAL FILE. 

There will be NOTHING physically mailed to you.

This is a 100% hand lettered, hand drawn DIGITAL FILE.

Any physical items shown in the listing photos are EXAMPLES of how you can use the digital files. 

All the lettering artwork in my shop is lovingly hand-drawn by me!

You can use digital files with cut machines like Silhouette, Cricut and Scan N Cut. They can also be used with endless computer programs that can merge, edit and print designs. It is YOUR responsibility to know if the files I provide will work with your program.

The digital formats you will receive include:

PDF
SVG
JPEG (8x11)
PNG
DXF

After purchasing, you will receive an email to download your files digitally in a ZIP file. You may also download from your “purchases” tab in Etsy.

Please see here for help downloading designs: https://help.etsy.com/hc/en-us/articles/115013328108?flash_digest=be3dbde9fffefbd8aa95a7c04e1417e004a7efaf

There are watermarks (opaque lines) on my art in the example photos, the art that you purchase will not have these lines on it.

DIGITAL FILE LISCENCING/RULES:

You CAN:
 - print and/or cut for your unlimited personal use (personal use is defined as made for non-commercial, non-profit use)
- give away a printed out copy of the artwork (NOT the digital file)
- print/use them for ‘single classroom’ use
- sell an item YOU make yourself, with the file, up to 100 units.  You have to do the work yourself to make the item (for example, HTV on a t-shirt or bag, sublimation on a shirt or bag, etc.)

You CANNOT:
- gift or share the digital file through ANY electronic method (email, facebook, IG, etc)
- sell a physical item you make yourself more than 100 units - UNLESS you purchase an additional commercial license; please see an additional listing in my shop to purchase a commercial license 
- upload the design to ANY ‘file sharing’ websites 
- upload the design to a third party company and sell items that a company prints

Purchasing this file does not transfer rights to the buyer - I retain all rights to my artwork.

All of my artwork is registered with the copyright office. 
 
Thank you for reading and considering my shop!!

INSTRUCTIONS:

HOW TO INSTALL THE FONT ON PC OR MAC:

Unzip your font folder and double click on the font to install it.

*For Ipad and iPhone users, you can search on the "app store" some free "font manager" app, it is 100% compatible on IPad and iPhone as well.


///


CRICUT AND SILHOUETTE: (Instructions with images included in your download folder)

Please note. I do not offer support for Cricut, however, I provide you with some instructions bellow that might help you.

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON PC:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF). Double-click it!
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.
Congratulations! Your font is now installed.
Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!


///


HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON MAC OS X:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF).
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.

Congratulations! Your font is now installed.

Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!


///


HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE IN IOS 11 OR HIGHER ON AN IPAD OR IPHONE:

First, go to the app store and get a free app called iFont. Once you’re in the app store, click on the Search button down at the bottom and type in iFont. Click on the download icon. After the app finishes downloading, click to open iFont.

Download the font to your iPad or iPhone.

iFont should open with the Open Zip Archive screen. You should then be directed back to iFont. On the left, you’ll see an option to Install the Maker Penwriting Regular font. Tap the Install button. You’ll be guided through a series of menus. Tap Allow. Settings should open showing a window to Install Profile. Tap Install. You may be prompted for your device’s passcode. You may have to tap install a couple more times to complete the process. You should see a screen that says Profile Installed. Tap Done. The font is now installed on your device.

Restart the Cricut Design Space app. Click on the text at the bottom. Click on the All tab because of the app defaults to the Cricut tab. Type in the name of the font you just installed. Tap on it. You should now be back at the Canvas screen. Type in text to see what it looks like.


///


HOW TO MANUALLY INSTALL FONTS FOR SILHOUETTE:


Note: You do not need to download the font into the Silhouette software. Once the Mia font is installed on your computer in your font directory, the font will show up as an available option for cutting letters once the Silhouette software is opened.


INSTALL THE FONT ON A PC:

1. After you purchase the font, your font will be available to download. Right-click on the font link from Etsy and "Save link as" to your computer. A zipped folder will be downloaded to your default download location on your computer. It will be named "Mia Font Commercial.zip" on your PC:

Depending on your download environment, the download may show in the downloads section of your browser OR in the default download location

Open the downloaded folder

2. Double-click on "Mia Font Commercial.zip" folder to install (A font management window will open)

3. Select the Install option in the upper-left of the window

4. The Install button will turn grey, indicating that the font has been installed


INSTALL THE FONT ON A MAC:

1. After you purchase the font, a zipped folder will be available and downloaded to your default download location on your computer. It will be named "Mia Font Commercial.zip" on your PC:

Depending on your download environment, the download may show in the downloads section of your browser OR in the default download location

Open the downloaded folder

2. Double-click on "Mia Font Commercial.zip" folder to install (A font management window will open)

3. Select the Install option in the lower-right of the window

4. The font management window will close, indicating that the font has been installed

Voila! :)

title: Hibiscus Ultra Opal POWDER Exquisite Translucent Dichroic Fuchsia Chameleon Art Pigments
description:
* "Hibiscus Ultra Opal" now in powder form! It is an exquisite powder in the same hues as our Flake version, but somehow, this powder is a bit more magical with its luxe brilliant color intensity. It's gorgeous! This luster powder has a strong, bright color shift on a colored translucent substrate which gives it a "satiny" smooth, soft effect feel on skin and other materials. The next generation in amazing color shifting, ultra-rich and high chroma flake product! 

* IT IS EXTREMELY LIGHTWEIGHT FLUFFY POWDER, so we're selling them with three different size containers. A full gram fills our medium size jar (see photo sizes) to the rim. Our half gram fills our small jar, and our sample bag is about .20 gram of powder to test out. 

* Cosmetic safe for eyes and face too! Brilliant reflective dichroic reflection with color changing qualities depending on viewed angle are NON_PLASTIC. Made with a silica-based micron thin glass substrate with prismatic metallic oxides fused to the surface. Our flakes work more like fine foil or gold leaf on many different mediums. Solvent safe, and great for body and nail art! A little goes a long way.

* Transparent flakes look dramatic over dark bases, & completely different over light ones.

*Check out our Hibiscus Flake version here; https://www.etsy.com/listing/986638918/hibiscus-ultra-opal-flake-transparent?click_key=916018515db3404c35f5079976d82b2cec79932a%3A986638918&click_sum=b94fff13&ref=shop_home_active_22&sts=1

* The gorgeous feather tray was made with epoxy resin by our dear friends at ResinateBR, llc. The colors featured here for embellishments are Amazon Ultra Opal Flake, Blue Hawaii Ultra Opal Flake and our Pharaoh's Gold Ultra Fine chrome pigment for detail. Visit their shop on Instagram; @resinatebr .

———
 FAQ
———

“Can I use mail merge to fill in my template?”
At this time, no. But in our experience it only takes about 20 minutes to copy and paste addresses for 100 people (ie. about the same amount of time it takes to figure out mail merge). If you're pressed for time, this is a great task to ask a bridesmaid to help with.

“Can I change the template size?"
Sadly, no, not at this time.

"How many address labels can I print per page"
These labels come 5 to a sheet.

"Can I change the colors?"
Artwork colors are fixed and can’t be changed. But you CAN change solid backgrounds, lines, borders and text colors.

"Do I have to use Avery 22838 Wraparound Address Labels with this?"
No, you can print these out on either full US Letter sticker paper or plain printer paper and trim them out using scissors. We can't guarantee they'll work with any other pre-cut address labels, aside from Avery 22838.

"Can I change the fonts?"
Yes! You can choose from an extensive list of fonts provided in Templett.

"Can I add an image or artwork? Can I delete artwork?"
Yup! We tell you how in the instructions.

"What file types should I download?"
We recommend downloading and printing these as a PDF.



HAVE MORE QUESTIONS? Send us a message! We'd love to hear from you.

title: Delta Bribri limited edition fountain pen- unused
description:
In 2003 Delta inaugurated the series of writing instruments called "Indigenous People" which were dedicated to indigenous populations all over the world who have safeguarded their traditions and style of life.
The first limited edition was dedicated to the Masai population and many others were manufactured in the following years.
The Bribri limited edition was issued in 2014 and was dedicated to the Aborigenal population of Costa Rica who were granted the right to live in a special reserve in 1977. 
The Bribri population is known as the "Happy People" as they live in perfect harmony with their environment. The area where they live is known to have more than 100 different species of frogs. These small amphibious animals share their life with the Bribris and they are considered by the indigenous people as " living jewels".
The Bribri limited edition is full of symbolic meanings: the small frog on the clip is clearly dedicated to the several species of frogs inhabiting the Bribri reserve in Costa Rica; the cap band reproduces the pattern of an indigenous mask and the cap top is decorated with a replica of a pre-Colombian medallion.
The Bribri limited edition was manufactured in 977 pieces with rhodiated finish and 977 with gold finish.
This Bribri pen is unused and it comes with its compete packaging.
The pen is a piston filler and it is fitted with a Delta Fusion nib, grade F.

EUROPEAN BUYERS PLEASE GET IN TOUCH BEFORE YOU BUY.

For more vintage and modern pens, please visit my website www.Tenpen.it

Thank you!

title: Songbird - Suminagashi - Bird Nature Print - Gyotaku reproduction - traditional Japanese art by Dwight Hwang
description:
***For information regarding the art, the artist and higher-end original prints, please visit my site at:
https://fishingforgyotaku.com/

Gyotaku and Suminagashi, two traditional techniques combined on a subject that isn't normally used with either. Like a centuries old classical sumie painting, a small songbird rests atop a twig of flowing ink.

Makes a great gift for that special bird enthusiast, Asian art collector or nature lover or any one who loves birds and appreciates this combination of two unique Japanese art forms.

Gyotaku is the traditional Japanese alternative to Taxidermy that began several hundred years ago by an ingenious calligrapher.  Meant as a way to record a proud catch for fishermen, it is also a stunning art form.  All of my prints are done in the old, traditional "direct" method where Sumi ink is applied directly onto the fish and then covered with Washi paper to produce an exact, mirror image of the specimen. 

All of the reproduction prints that I offer are museum grade Giclee prints on premium art rag papers such as Somerset Velvet or Epson Premium, both of which are similar in feel to hot pressed watercolor paper.  Most are printed in-house, while larger reproductions are drop shipped via a third party printing house using the same exact materials.

If you like one of my images but prefer it in a different size, simply inquire and I will do my best to cater to your wishes.  Anything is possible up to 60 inches, as well as printing on different materials such as canvas or even Japanese washi paper.

Prints will ship first class via tubes for protection.

Please don't hesitate in contacting me regarding this print or other specimens that you may be looking for!

title: Monogram Crest Wedding Invitations with RSVP Card, Calligraphy Monogram Wedding Invite with Envelopes and Details Card
description:
Check out these gorgeous wedding invitations with a calligraphy monogram crest! Invitations set the tone for your wedding day and a good invite can really get guests excited. Make sure you grab matching day-of items like menus and ceremony programs! For this design, I have a few other wreath/crest designs available upon request.

Digitally printed (single sided) invitations with your choice of paper and envelopes. Our standard, default paper is 120# ultra white eggshell-finish card stock. (Taylor collection)

INCLUDED IN YOUR SUITE:
-- 2-piece suite includes a 5x7 invitation card with envelope
-- 3-piece suite includes a 5x7 invitation card with envelope and a 4.25x5.5 or smaller insert card
-- 4-piece suite includes a 5x7 invitation card with envelope and a 3.5x5 response card with envelope
-- 5-piece suite includes a 5x7 invitation card with envelope, 3.5x5 response card with envelope, and a 4.25x5.5 or smaller insert card

Sample suite is a non-personalized 5-piece suite on our standard paper with white envelopes and a swatch card of ink colors for your convenience. Samples will be will shipped as regular mail without tracking.

UPGRADES
If you're interested in upgrades/add-ons such as envelope printing, extra insert cards, belly bands, vellum wrap, cotton paper, letterpress or gold foil printing, etc., please reach out thru Etsy message or email for a quote!

If you'd like to add wax seals, click here: https://www.etsy.com/shop/LottieLouStationery?ref=simple-shop-header-name&listing_id=868188516&section_id=30953644

To shop my other invitation designs, click here: https://www.etsy.com/shop/LottieLouStationery?ref=seller-platform-mcnav&section_id=30579495

For quantities larger than 250, please contact me :) (remember you only need to order one suite per family/household, NOT one for every guest.. plus a few extras for keepsakes!)

PROOFS
You should expect to receive a digital proof from me 1-2 business days after providing your details. Processing time after the first proof being sent largely depends on the customer. Your order includes 3 rounds of complementary proofs, each following round will add $10 to your order. Each round of proofs will take about 1 business day, so the more edits you make, the later your items will ship. Customer is responsible for responding to proofs in a timely manner.

SHIPPING
Items will be shipped directly from my printer in Alabama via Fedex Ground. Envelopes may be shipped separately. Once you've approved your final proof, printing will take 3-5 business days and shipping will take 4-5 business days or less for addresses in the continental US. Orders headed to Hawaii and Alaska will take about 7+ days to arrive. Rush fees for printing and expedited shipping are available; please reach out for a quote. Customer is responsible for any rush fees.

Lottie Lou Stationery is not responsible for non-deliverable packages or incorrect shipping addresses. Invitations ship via Fedex and are unable to be sent to PO boxes.

If you're working with a wedding planner, you can ask about getting your items shipped directly to them!

REFUNDS/RETURNS
Custom orders are nonrefundable and nonreturnable. If items become damaged during shipment, let me know ASAP so I can contact the printer. If your items do not match the final proof, let me know within 2 days and I will reprint the affected items free of charge, with the original shipping method, unless you'd like to pay for upgraded shipping. Customer is responsible for any rush fees.

Customer is responsible for accuracy of final proof. I will attempt to call out any errors and let you know if it seems like any details have been left out, but it is ultimately the customer's responsibility. This includes any spelling errors, inaccurate info, missing details, etc. If a reprint is needed due to an error on the approved proof, please let me know and I can set that up for you.

Feel free to contact me via Etsy or by emailing LottieLou.Stationery@gmail.com

title: IC13 Intense Colorshift Pigment Gen2 Hi Quality Chameleon Mirror Chrome KolorEFX Powder
description:
Rich Intense color-shifting pigments can add value and appeal to products where color is a key differentiating factor.  
They also have the added ability to create a multichrome mirror effect when properly applied over a UV gel base.

Our pearl pigments can be mixed with oil and water-based products.

Some Popular Uses
        Paints - Glazes – Acrylics – Epoxy Resins - Gel Coats
        Auto Coatings - Clearcoats, Liquid wraps
        Concrete - Pottery - Countertops & Floors
        Nail Art - Candles - Slime - Polymer Clay
        Arts & Crafts – Airbrushing - Inks
        Faux Finishing on Funiture
        Reborn Art - Jewelry
        Fishing Lures and Countless others

They have Good Dispersion Performance and High Color Strength

Try the 1g samples available in your application.
Larger quantities may be available upon request!

Please note to achieve the best color-shifting effects apply over black/dark base coat.


How to use to get a mirror chrome effect on nails : 
1. Apply UV GEL base color to nails. Black works best. Cure under LED/UV Light.
2. Apply Gel Clear Top Coat. Cure under LED/UV Light.
3. Use a sponge-tipped eyeshadow stick to pick up the powder and apply it to your nails. A little goes a long way, so don't use too much. 
    Evenly smear onto the nail, rubbing back and forth until the desired result is achieved.
4. Lightly brush off excess powder. Seal it with No-wipe UV TOP COAT. Cure under LED/UV Light.

title: Master Class Copperplate Practice Sheets: From Basic Strokes to Complete Compositions
description:
This 40 page PDF workbook is a beginner friendly “one stop shop” for learning Copperplate calligraphy. All of the relevant information in one place and everything you need to practice to learn this script. Grab a pointed pen (list of my recommended tools here) and print this PDF on some good paper, and in an afternoon you will be proud of how far you’ve come.

This 40 page PDF workbook covers:

- Tools you’ll need
- Introduction to pointed pen – Absolute basics and how to get started
- Introduction to Copperplate Calligraphy – What makes it look so fancy?
- The 7 basic strokes
- 3 Methods on Creating Flat tops and Bottoms on your Letters
- Copperplate Drills
- Lowercase alphabet with stroke order, pressure and direction (26 Letters)
- Uppercase alphabet with stroke order, pressure and direction (26 Letters)
- Proper Connection of Letters Practice
- Best practice words and sentences (12 Words)
- Sentence practice page
- The 5 Guidelines of Flourishing with examples
- Letter Flourishes and Abstract Flourishes
- Composition Practice
- Create your Copperplate Composition
- Certificate of Completion
-Troubleshooting (2 pages of common problems and the best way to solve them to get you writing again.)
- BONUS 4 Pages - Copperplate Numbers (0-9)

With the willingness to learn, this practice book, and practice time, you will able to write your own Copperplate calligraphy compositions. I guarantee it.

If you have any problems, questions or feedback, please don’t hesitate to send me a message at richard@calligrascape.com.

Your support is very much appreciated!
