title: Personalized Gift for Her Bar Necklace. Calligraphy Stamped Custom Name Bar Necklace. Mother's Bar Necklace. Hand Lettering. Gifts for her.
description:
Personalize your own high quality bar necklace with our beautiful Calligraphy Font #9.  Choose from 14k Gold-Filled, Rose Gold-Filled, or Sterling Silver.  Select the font that speaks to you and create a one of a kind piece with your words of choice.


To Order:
1. Select your Bar Size & Material from the 1st drop down menu

2. Select your Necklace Length from the 2nd drop down menu (this is total length including the bar.)

3. In the personalization box, please provide any other information I will need to create your piece.  Words, Symbol(s), Font, and Alignment (centered or right aligned.)  If you are unsure of anything, just let me know and I can help you select what will work best for your design. 

4. Once you are viewing your cart during checkout, there is another box where you can submit a note to me if there is any additional info I need to know.  **Please double check your shipping address before submitting your order!**


Keep reading below for more info about materials and our process.
<><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><>


OUR MATERIALS:

Gold-Filled: 
REAL 14k Gold thickly bonded to a base metal core. It is up to 100x thicker than plated jewelry. It is generally acceptable for anyone with sensitive skin to wear. I personally have highly sensitive skin and am able to wear all of our metals without any issues at all. Gold-filled does not tarnish. It features all of the benefits of wearing real gold at a fraction of the cost. The base metal is never exposed, so there is no difference that the eye can see. The color is a beautiful bright gold and looks especially beautiful on warm & dark skin tones.

Rose-Gold Filled: 
REAL Rose Gold thickly bonded to a base metal core. It is up to 100x thicker than plated jewelry. In order to get the pink color, a small amount of copper is added to the gold. This can occasionally cause reactions in people with highly sensitive skin, but it is such a small amount that it generally is ok. Rose Gold-Filled does not tarnish and is an absolutely beautiful color. It looks great mixed with Silver and is especially beautiful on cool & light skin tones. 

Sterling Silver:
Real .925 grade solid Sterling Silver. All silver tarnishes and Sterling Silver is no exception. Interestingly, it has a great bit to do with personal body PH levels. Some people with alkaline bodies can wear silver and it will look new forever, others can turn a piece in a matter of days if they are more acidic. Either way, silver can be easily cleaned with our polishing pads included in each purchase. These pads can also be purchased in our shop if needed.

CARE:
In order to preserve your item’s longevity, please remove your necklace when you take a shower, go for a swim, or work out. Sweat, chlorine water, and perfume can cause Sterling to tarnish quickly as well as cause the ink to fade on all metals. If your necklace gets wet it will not ruin it, but it is very helpful to dry it off as soon as possible. **Please avoid spraying perfume or applying lotion while wearing the necklace. Remove your jewelry first, apply perfume/lotion, then put your jewelry back on after application has absorbed into your skin.** With proper care these necklaces should last for many years.

PACKAGING:
Each item is will arrive in a small box with a bow and ready for giving. If you purchase multiple items, please check the bottoms of the boxes as we always mark them for easy identification.  We also offer a gift-wrap upgrade for $1 that includes a hand written gift card (left blank if no gift message is provided), luxury satin ribbon, and decorative washi tape.

WHY PURCHASE FROM US? 
This is our full-time passion. I (Brianna) started making jewelry when I was only 8 years old and I have lived & breathed it ever since. Two years ago my husband (Seth) quit his job and joined me full-time and together we put our whole hearts into creating what we hope will be a fantastic shopping experience for you. From start to finish, our goal is to create art that inspires and has significant meaning for you, hence our business name *Words By Heart*. 
Each bar is hand-cut by us in our workshop. We use 20 gauge metal, which is heavier/thicker than the widely used 24 gauge. This enables our bars to hold up longer than most bars on the market. Our chain is sturdy and sparkling. Providing you with a high quality product that you can feel good about is very important to us! We do not skimp on quality and purchase all of our metal, supplies, & tools from other small businesses within the USA. When you support us, you also support a whole network of small family-owned businesses here in America. 

OUR GUARANTEE:
We know sometimes things can get lost in transit - that is why we guarantee delivery of all items. If it is lost we will replace it.
We want you to have a 5-star experience every time you shop with us. If you don’t absolutely LOVE your purchase, please contact us and we will work with you to make sure you leave as happy as possible. 

** This necklace is HAND STAMPED by me. Hand Stamping is very different than engraving. It requires a hammer and a metal stamp, which has a single letter on the end of it. Each letter is then hammered into the metal one by one - by hand, and therefore is not machine precise. The result is a beautifully unique piece each and every time. **

Questions? Contact me through Etsy Convos and I will be happy to help!

MORE BAR NECKLACES
https://www.etsy.com/shop/wordsbyheartco/search?search_query=bar+necklaces&order=date_desc&view_type=gallery&ref=shop_search

BACK TO SHOP
https://www.etsy.com/shop/wordsbyheartco?ref=hdr_shop_menu

All of our prints are made from high resolution photos and printed using only high quality sublimation paper and inks. All of our designs are created in house or purchased from a variety of artisans worldwide which include commercial licensing rights.

Sublimation transfers require a heat press and properly coated sublimation products and are good for ONE time use only.

Please note that white colours do not sublimate. Any white parts of the transfer will take on the colour of the actual substrate. For example, if pressing onto a purple shirt, any white spots in the transfer were show as purple.

We recommend measuring your substrates to make sure our transfers will fit before ordering. If you need a custom size, please select custom and include the measurements in the personalization box.

♥♥♥ HOW TO APPLY♥♥♥
Recommendations for applying the labels with optimal adhesion: 

- Clean your hands and the destination surface. Any debris, dust, moisture, or natural oils can interfere with the adhesive, weakening the bond.  If soap solution has spilled and dried on the containers and these are not cleaned, the stickers won't stick or they will start to pill off right after applying them.

- Apply the center of the label first and then work out toward the edges. This reduces some of the tension on the ends of the label which will help it stay down.

- Use pressure when sticking the labels to your surface. Our products are pressure-sensitive, so more pressure equates to a stronger bond.

♥♥♥ HOW TO ORDER ♥♥♥

***PLEASE READ BEFORE ORDERING:  This listing is for LABELS ONLY, containers ARE NOT included***

1. On the dropdown menu:
    - Choose foil color or black ink

2. Leave names and date for personalization.  


*If you want a proof, please request in the “Add a note to seller” section.  We’ll send within 3 business days to your etsy messages and will ship in 2-3 business days after approval.  Proof will be sent in black ink.  Please make sure you check your etsy messages or email and approve it. Non-proofed items will be processed and shipped faster*

**Please include all the information needed to process your order.  Not doing so will delay your order.  We will process your order when we receive the information from you**

*** Please note that not every name will look exactly like the one shown in this listing, as the font differs between letters. We will try to make it as close as possible and if we need to do mayor changes we will send you a digital proof first to make sure you like it***

***If you would like to make any changes to a listing or there is something specific that you cannot see in our listings please contact us to discuss further***

♥♥♥ SHOP POLICIES ♥♥♥ 

Thank you for choosing Ink Your Style. We take pride in our products and services and want you to have confidence in us. We value you as a customer and your complete satisfaction is our priority, please contact us if you are not completely satisfied with our products.

 Due to the customization and timing involved in every order, we do not accept cancelations beyond two hours of placing the order. Once shipped, USPS provides a tracking number for all of our packages, Ink your Style IS NOT responsible for lost, damaged or delayed shipments, please contact your local USPS office directly for any inquiry.

  ♥ Processing time, Shipping and delivery

Due to the customization, items are shipped 3-5 business days after an order is placed or a proof has been approved (If requested). Items that are shipped Within the U.S are shipped via USPS first class mail (usually takes 2-5 days). Customers have the option to upgrade shipping to USPS priority mail (usually takes 2-3 days), USPS express priority mail (1-2 days) or Fedex 1 or 2 days. title: Your name in Japanese calligraphy  | Personalized Japanese Name | Japanese art |  | Japanese wall decor | Japanese gifts | Japanese art
description:
YOUR NAME IN JAPANESE CALLIGRAPHY 

The symbols or characters created in the Japanese calligraphy arts are known as 'kanji'. 

They are drawn with a series of vertical, horizontal, and angled brushstrokes, and each symbol or character is unique. 

There are more than 10,000 of Kanji, each with a specific meaning. 

There are symbols for words or ideas, like luck, peace, and happiness, and for things, like dog, horse, fire, and volcano.

We will convert your English name to Japanese using phonetic translation - the pronunciation of the name is used to translate the name, not the spelling. 
Then we will pick the meaningful symbols for your name from thousands of kanjis. 



• • • DETAILS• • • 
▪ Your Name in Japanese Calligraphy

title: Salute The Troops with the Stars and Stripes
description:
This was a slightly difficult pen for me.  Took four attempts to get two pens turned and fitted properly.  I think I have it now.  Anyway, it came out nice.  The other pen is already spoken for and will be used by an active Air Force aerial gunner - cool!

So, in addition to the work I did on creating the stars and stripes, this pen features a handsome etched engraving of a saluting soldier, an American Flag on on the tip, and the words "SALUTE THE TROOPS" stamped on the cap end. The patriotic theme is continued on the pen clip which features a red, white and blue American Flag and handsomely cast Bald Eagle emblem.  This pen also features a bolt action mechanism with a 30 caliber copper bullet tip.

To honor the American Troops, Penn State Industries will donate one Slimline Pen Kit to the "Freedom Pen Project" for every Salute the Troops Pen Kit sold. The Freedom pen project sends handmade pens to American servicemen and women overseas to show appreciation and support for their time and duty spent defending our country.

description:
Say hello to our brand new Modern Wedding Invite range! The big day is coming and it's time to tell your guests all about it! With handpicked papers and stunning fonts you can't go wrong with these simple yet beautiful invitations.

All of our products are printed in house by our team and dispatched directly to you, Why bother getting a digital download and having the stress of getting it printed? We take care of everything for you, once you approve the design we dispatch the same day!

I LOVE THE DESIGN, WHAT SHOULD I DO NEXT?
Just follow our simple steps below!

1) Choose the pack size you would like to purchase from the drop down menu (Keep the quantity as 1)!

2) Purchase! Once you have purchased you will be sent an email that will direct you to our easy to use personalisation form where you can send us your personalisation details, Choose from our envelopes, Submit photos and any other special requirements you might have!

3) Our design team will send you a digital proof to check over before printing (Unlimited revisions included!) Once approved we will get your order printed, packaged and posted out straight to your front door, Its that simple!

PRINTING:
We digitally print all of our invitations in house on beautifully hand picked papers that complement our wedding stationery and ship them directly to your door, stress free!

PAPERS:
Our Simple & Beautiful Wedding Invite is printed on a premium 350gsm Bianco Matte Card straight from the exclusive Fedrigoni range (only the best!) It is fully recycled Matte card with a beautifully subtle texture, perfect for printing, perfect for writing & perfect for showing off!

SIZE:
Our wedding invites are 5x7 as standard, a perfect size! Want to discuss a custom size? No problem, just give us a call on 01227 656 586 or drop us a message and we will see what we can do!

ENVELOPES:
All of our orders include FREE envelopes, you just need to choose which ones are right for you! This listing does NOT include envelope printing, if you would like to enquire about this please get in touch via Etsy message or email us at hello [!at] wanderluststudio.uk for a quote.

DELIVERY & TURNAROUND TIMES:
All of our products include FREE delivery, Wanderlust Studio is based in the 'Garden of England' but don't worry we have a long reach! We can deliver to Australia, Canada, USA and many other beautiful places! Our shipping turnaround times are below. 

United Kingdom: 1 - 2 working days!
Europe: 3 - 4 working days!
United States of America & Canada: 7 - 10 working days!
Australia: 7 - 14 working days!

Need your order delivered more quickly? We offer express shipping too! Please get in touch for a quotation. 

ARE WE MISSING ANYTHING?
If there is anything you are unsure about or you would like to chat to our team about your invitations then great! We love to hear from you and help in anyway we can, Our details are below.

P: 01227 656 586
E: hello [!at] wanderluststudio.uk

Looking for some wedding stationery inspiration to help you plan your own wedding? Our sample packs have everything you'll need to create your perfect invitations and day-of stationery for your big day! 

You will receive a mix of our favourite designs printed on our range of high-quality paper. Please be aware that our sample packs are not personalised.

title: Placecards - Navy blue, gold or white ink, modern calligraphy, party decor, event decor, hand lettering, handwriting, place setting
description:
***This listing is strictly for information.  A custom listing will be created when you are ready to order.

***This listing is only for DARK BLUE place cards.  Any other color must be discussed and may possibly take longer to finish due to ordering supplies.

You can use place cards as escort cards for guests or even to label various foods or items on any buffet/table spread.  The possibilities are endless!

Turn around time should be fairly quick because these place cards will be cut and scored (if needed) by me.  There will be no need for purchasing place cards and waiting for their arrival.  All the supplies are here and ready to go!

I offer two styles to choose from: flat and tented
I offer two ink colors to choose from: gold and white

FLAT:
These place cards can lie flat on the table or can be placed in a place card holder.  
Measurements: 3.5 inches wide x 2 inches length

TENTED:
These place cards are meant to be folded and should be able to stand on their own.  These place cards are shipped with a score line down the middle where buyer will fold when ready to display.
Measurements upon delivery: 3.5 inches wide x 4 inches length.  The score line will be at 2 inches.
Measurements after folding: 3.5 inches wide x 2 inches tall

***Because these are hand cut by me, adjustments in size can be discussed to better fit your party needs***

Purchasing process:
The process can start by sending me a custom order request.  We can discuss quantity, style, and turn around time.  Once details are finalized, I will create a custom listing for you.  Once payment is received, I will request the list of names and other information you'd like on the place cards, preferably in the Excel spreadsheet I will provide.  Please make sure to proof read the list.  I will be writing things exactly as they are given to me.  When the list of names and information is received, I can begin the place card production process.  

Add-ons not paid for:
Upon purchase, you are allowed FIVE free add-ons. Once the sixth or more add on is requested, I will charge you for ALL the add-ons in a separate custom listing. 

Unused placecards already paid for:
Once place cards are completed and the final count is LESS THAN the amount of placecards you paid for, I will refund you the difference. Ex. You paid for 100, but only ended up with 95. I will refund you the 5 placecards

Cancellations:
In case of cancellation, buyer will be responsible for paying all the completed place cards.  I will refund for the cost of the amount of place cards that had not been written yet.  

Shipping will be adjusted on an order to order basis.  

Please feel free to contact me with any questions or concerns.

- This listing does not include a graduation cap.

application instructions

- CLEAN YOUR SURFACE OF ANY DEBRIS AND SMOOTH ANY WRINKLES.
- USING A CREDIT CARD, MAKE SURE THE DECAL IS COMPLETELY ADHERED TO THE CLEAR TRANSFER TAPE. 
- SLOWLY PULL THE TRANSFER TAPE OFF THE PAPER BACKING. IF ANY PART OF THE DECAL IS NOT STICKING TO THE TRANSFER TAPE, REPEAT THE PREVIOUS STEP.
- CAREFULLY POSITION AND PLACE THE TRANSFER TAPE ONTO YOUR CAP. STARTING FROM THE CENTER AND WORKING YOUR WAY OUTWARDS, USE YOUR THUMBS TO FIRMLY SMOOTH THE TRANSFER TAPE ONTO YOUR CAP. MAKE SURE THE VINYL IS TOTALLY ADHERED TO YOUR SURFACE AND THERE ARE NO AIR BUBBLES.
- SLOWLY PEEL OFF THE CLEAR TRANSFER TAPE AND YOUR NEW DECAL IS GOOD TO GO!

CRICUT AND SILHOUETTE:

Please note. I do not offer support for Cricut, however, I provide you with some instructions bellow that might help you.

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON PC:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF). Double-click it!
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.
Congratulations! Your font is now installed.
Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!



HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON MAC OS X:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF).
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.

Congratulations! Your font is now installed.

Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE IN IOS 11 OR HIGHER ON AN IPAD OR IPHONE:

First, go to the app store and get a free app called iFont. Once you’re in the app store, click on the Search button down at the bottom and type in iFont. Click on the download icon. After the app finishes downloading, click to open iFont.

Download the font to your iPad or iPhone.

iFont should open with the Open Zip Archive screen. You should then be directed back to iFont. On the left, you’ll see an option to Install the Maker Penwriting Regular font. Tap the Install button. You’ll be guided through a series of menus. Tap Allow. Settings should open showing a window to Install Profile. Tap Install. You may be prompted for your device’s passcode. You may have to tap install a couple more times to complete the process. You should see a screen that says Profile Installed. Tap Done. The font is now installed on your device.

Restart the Cricut Design Space app. Click on the text at the bottom. Click on the All tab because of the app defaults to the Cricut tab. Type in the name of the font you just installed. Tap on it. You should now be back at the Canvas screen. Type in text to see what it looks like.


///


HOW TO MANUALLY INSTALL FONTS FOR SILHOUETTE:

Open the downloaded folder

title: Classic, Elegant Wedding Invitation Suite with Greenery  | Formal Extra Thick Printed Floral Wedding Invites | Adele
description:
If your wedding is formal, traditional and elegant, this classic floral wedding invitation will be a perfect way to invite your family and friends. This design features uses one of my favorite calligraphy fonts that pairs beautifully with delicate greenery. Add in a beautiful envelope liner and belly band to complete the look. I'm always open to custom orders, so if you have different paper colors or styles in mind, just let me know! 

I'll take care of the printing and worry about those details so you get the best paper, nothing flimsy!

This set is modern and traditional, and will be sure to impress your guests with its classic beauty.

*vintage notecards are a photo prop and are not available for purchase.

✨WHY THESE ARE RIGHT FOR YOU ✨
When I got married, I was frustrated. I flipped through book after book and nothing was quite right. A lot were almost right and all I wanted to do is combine a few designs together to create something perfect. That's what I strive to do with each and every wedding that I work with. If you want to merge design elements from 2 suites together, great! If you want to add in a colored envelope or a wax seal or a vellum wrap - we can do that! You're working one on one with a designer that can change those things to make these uniquely you. I don't have a limit to the number of revisions you get, that's not how I want to run my business. We'll make it perfect.

✨EXTRAS THAT ARE ALWAYS INCLUDED ✨
- unlimited rounds of proofs
- paper swatches mailed out to you if you would like to see your options
- complimentary printed proofs (if time allows - they take about 2 weeks)
- your address printed on the RSVP envelope
- your return address printed on the mailing envelope

**printed guest addresses are an additional $0.75
✨WHAT MAKES THESE SPECIAL✨
My favorite part of the classic collection is the paper. I'm a bit of a paper snob and I've tried all the papers. I have these printed a crisp, 120# Mohawk Superfine cardstock in either white or ivory, OR you can upgrade the invites to a double thick 240# weight for extra luxurious design.

Double thick cardstock is quite literally - twice the thickness. These invitations are printed on 240 lb cardstock with an eggshell texture. They feel luxurious in your hands and will make such a great impression to your guests. It's roughly the thickness of a paper coaster. 

You can see all of the designs in the double thick collection here - https://etsy.me/2zuLrjq

✨SAMPLES✨
Samples are always available and typically ship within 2-3 days. If I'm out of stock I'll contact you with an updated ship date. Samples will include the invite, info card, RSVP, belly band, envelope liner and samples of both single and double thick paper in white and ivory.

If you have any custom requests that you don't see from the dropdown menu, please send me a message with details so I can further advise you on any additional costs.

• full invitation wording exactly as you'd like it on your invitation

Nothing is printed without your approval!

Your proofs will arrive via your Etsy account, so please either check into Etsy frequently or turn on your conversation email notifications. If I don't hear from you within 48 hours, I will also reach out through email. 

Proofs will be sent to you in a PDF formatted to print out at home on regular printer paper so you can see everything in real size.

If you have added guest address printing to your order, I will email you an Excel or Google Sheets (if requested) template required for your guest addresses. Please note that addresses must be provided in this template, I am not able to reformat them for you.

Your custom printed designs typically ship within 7-10 days of proof approval. All orders ship Priority Mail (2-3 days) unless we have discussed other options.

title: Black Lives Matter Bookmark | BLM Fundraiser | BLM Donation | Black Power Bookmark | Black Lives Matter Fundraiser | Activist Bookmark |
description:
Please help me support the BLM movement! 

This listing is for a Black Lives Matter hand-lettered bookmark. It is approximately 2" wide and 8" long. Each is handwritten by me and laminated to make sure it lasts a long time! The silver lettering really pops against the black paper. 

Half of all profits (proceeds minus cost of supplies, fees, etc.) will be donated to The Loveland Foundation. 

ABOUT THE LOVELAND FOUNDATION:
The Loveland Foundation was established in 2018 by Rachel Cargle in response to her widely successful birthday wish fundraiser, Therapy for Black Women and Girls. Her enthusiastic social media community raised over $250,000, which made it possible for Black women and girls nationally to receive therapy support. Black women and girls deserve access to healing, and that healing will impact generations.

The Loveland Foundation is the official continuation of this effort to bring opportunity and healing to communities of color, and especially to Black women and girls. Through fellowships, residency programs, listening tours, and more, ultimately we hope to contribute to both the empowerment and the liberation of the communities we serve.

www.thelovelandfoundation.org

title: Highland Hairy Cow Screen Print Transfer (Low Heat Formula) // Ready To Press
description:
Interested in more screen print, sublimation and HTV transfers? Join our Facebook group at https://www.facebook.com/groups/berkshireandwaytransfers for all our newest and upcoming transfers. You’ll be able to participate in group discussions, learn more about the transfer application process and make suggestions on new design ideas.

VETERAN OWNED SMALL BUSINESS! WE APPRECIATE EACH AND EVERY ORDER!

Listing: Highland Hairy Cow Screen Print Transfer

Printed: Plastisol Inks and Heat Transfer Paper

Graphic Design Color(s): Black (Low Heat Formula)

Design Size: Adult - 11"W

(Size is measured by the widest part of the design.  Please note that not all designs are going to be exact squares, some may be taller, some may be shorter.  However, all designs will be sized proportionally.)

This listing is for a PHYSICAL SCREEN PRINT TRANSFER. You WILL NOT receive a digital download. You will receive a ready to press screen print transfer.

What are Screen Print Transfers?

A screen print transfer (also known as a plastisol transfer) is an image which has been screen printed onto release paper. Instead of being directly screen printed onto a shirt or other item, the design is printed onto transfer paper, then applied with a heat press using heavy pressure.

These screen print transfers can be applied to 100% cotton, 100% polyester, and cotton/polyester blends on light and dark colored garments.

Screen print transfers must be applied with a heat press. They CANNOT be applied with an iron or any type of EasyPress because these devices do not allow enough even pressure needed to properly adhere the inks to the garment.

When applying a low heat screen print transfer, set your heat press temperature to 325 degrees Fahrenheit, the timer to 7-8 seconds, and the pressure to heavy.  (Please note your heat press should be difficult to open and close, but not impossible to open and close.  Screen print transfers require heavy pressure to allow the inks to properly adhere to the garment.  If enough pressure is not being used when pressing the screen print transfers, it will cause the inks to lift, crack and/or peel from the garment.  The most common mistake made when pressing the screen print transfers is not using enough pressure allowing the inks to properly adhere to the garment.)

Using a fresh adhesive, lint-roll the surface of your garment where you will be applying your design prior to prepressing to remove any lint.

Prepress your garment for 7-8 seconds to remove any wrinkles and moisture.

Place the screen print transfer face down onto the garment.  (The ink on the transfer should be facing down touching the garment, not the upper portion of your heat press platform.)

Press your garment at 325 degrees Fahrenheit for 7-8 seconds with HEAVY pressure.

Slowly peel off the transfer paper while the ink is still hot.  (These screen print transfers are designed to be peeled hot, not cold.)

(Optional: After pressing your transfer and slowly peeling off the transfer paper, we encourage you to reposition your garment on the heat press, lay a piece of parchment paper over the design, and pressing your garment again for another 7-8 seconds with heavy pressure.  This will ensure if there are any “cold spots” in your heat press, all areas of the design will get the proper amount of heat exposure and pressure allowing the inks to properly adhere to the garment and will prevent the inks from lifting, cracking and/or peeling.)

We do not recommend using Teflon sheets, butcher paper and/or pillows when initially pressing your transfer, only during the second press.

For more information on the Low Heat Screen Print Application Process:  https://berkshireandway.com/pages/low-heat-screen-print-transfer-application-instructions

By purchasing this listing you agree to having some knowledge of the screen print process and how to use a transfer. I have outlined instructions within this listing but assume you understand the application process.

We DO NOT accept any returns or exchanges on screen print transfers. You may email us at customerservice@berkshireandway.com or send us a direct message with any questions you may have prior to purchasing any of the screen print transfers.

This is the text of the poem:
These are the hands of your best friend, young and strong and full of love,
that hold yours on your wedding day.
These are the hands that will work along side yours as you build your future together.
These are the hands that will passionately love you and care for you throughout the years.
These are the hands that will hold you when fear or grief torments your mind
and with the slightest touch, will comfort you like no other.
These are the hands that will give you strength when you struggle,
and support and encouragement to chase down your dreams.
These are the hands that will tenderly hold your children, and help keep your family together as one.
These are the hands that will, countless times, wipe the tears from yours eyes,
tears of sorrow, and tears of joy.
And lastly, these are the hands that even when wrinkled with age, will still be reaching for yours,
still giving you the same unspoken tenderness with just a touch---- a touch from these hands

Digital font, calligraphy font, digital font, download font, script font, swash font, swirly font, creative artwork font, Christmas font, Wedding font, Tattoo font, Thanksgiving font, Halloween font, monogram font, Cricut font, Wedding | Valentine's day


*****

INSTRUCTIONS:

How to install on PC or MAC:

Unzip your font folder and double click on the font to install it.

*For Ipad and iPhone users, you can search on the "app store" some free "font manager" app, it is 100% compatible on IPad and iPhone as well.


*****


Please note. I do not offer support for Cricut, however, I provide you bellow some instruction that might help you.

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON PC:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF). Double-click it!
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.
Congratulations! Your font is now installed.
Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON MAC OS X:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF).
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.

Congratulations! Your font is now installed.

Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE IN IOS 11 OR HIGHER ON AN IPAD OR IPHONE:

First, go to the app store and get a free app called iFont. Once you’re in the app store, click on the Search button down at the bottom and type in iFont. Click on the download icon. After the app finishes downloading, click to open iFont.

Download the font to your iPad or iPhone.

iFont should open with the Open Zip Archive screen. You should then be directed back to iFont. On the left, you’ll see an option to Install the Maker Penwriting Regular font. Tap the Install button. You’ll be guided through a series of menus. Tap Allow. Settings should open showing a window to Install Profile. Tap Install. You may be prompted for your device’s passcode. You may have to tap install a couple more times to complete the process. You should see a screen that says Profile Installed. Tap Done. The font is now installed on your device.

Restart the Cricut Design Space app. Click on the text at the bottom. Click on the All tab because of the app defaults to the Cricut tab. Type in the name of the font you just installed. Tap on it. You should now be back at the Canvas screen. Type in text to see what it looks like.

title: BLAH 1.0 Painting
description:
Description 1: Scrolling and swiping on Facebook, Instagram and Youtube you see after a while the same shit over and over again. Different pictures, videos, news, but still all the information looks kind of the same, it becomes a white noise and just BLAH BLAH BLAH!

Using Lunatic's special calligraffiti (calligraphy + graffiti) style, I wanted to express my observations of you earthlings from the moon.

Criticizing information overload by creating another content - how ironically, I know!


Description 2: Inspired by Armin van Buuren's track "Blah Blah Blah".


Size: 60 x 40 cm / 23.6 x 15.7 in

Created: May 2019


Composition:

Layer 0: 280 g/sqm canvas on wood frame

Layer 1: blue, red and yellow acrylic paint

Layer 2: partially covered with mattest and flattest acrylic black - Black 2.0 by Culturehustle

Layer 3: different versions of "B" using Lunatic's calligraffiti style and 10 mm black marker by Montana (mtn)

Layer 4: "BLAH BLAH BLAH" using Lunatic's calligraffiti style and 15 mm silver marker by Montana (mtn)

Layer 5: moon dust




Regards, 

Lunatic.

title: Winter - Handmade Metallic Watercolour Paint Shimmer Watercolor Handlettering, Calligraphy Ink, Silver Blue Watercolour, Grey Metallic Paint
description:
"Winter" is a silver-blue grey, with a light blue shine in light.

This colour is part of the Silver Grey palette, which is available as a tin with 3 other silver greys, and as half pans or quarter pans.

Made from the highest quality ingredients.

The binder is handmade and the paints are mulled befofe being poured into pans multiple times.

There is no filler used - just the mica pigment and binder.

NEW: Please select the option for a magnet or no magnet. If you select "yes", a magnet will be glued on the bottom of the pan, allowing it to be placed into metal palettes and stay in place. If you select "no", no magnet will be attached. The magnet does not affect use.

The pans are filled over a series of weeks, and allowed to dry fully inbetween to ensure you have the most amount of paint on each pan. Despite sitting over the pans for more hours than I wish to admit, air bubbles may occur and can be evident on the top of the pan. This does not affect the quality of the paints.

These paints work best after "activation". All you need to do is add a few drops of water to the top, let it sit for 2-3 minutes, rewet your brush and off you go!

The environment is important. At ArchiesPaints, we use fully recyclable packaging. Please recycle your packaging once you receive your order.

title: Matthew 5:4 of The Holy Bible (King James Version/KJV), art print of hand-lettered calligraphy suitable for framing
description:
This is a hand-signed print of Matthew 5:4 of The Holy Bible (King James Version/KJV), originally lettered in Old English style by Master Calligrapher Gary Labow in 2019. It is lettered in black ink.

This is a high-quality art print suitable for framing and comes with several print medium options:
- 100-pound cover stock paper, 270gsm (White)
- 65-pound text paper, 176gsm (Aged Parchment)
- 80-pound text paper, 216gsm (Gold Parchment)

100-pound Cover Stock is great for framing and is also durable enough to be displayed resting on a table-top stand. 80 or 65-pound Text Paper may be able to stand on its own but is less durable than cover stock and is best when framed.

Please note: this is a hand-lettered piece of professional calligraphy so there will be a natural variation from letter to letter. This is not a computer-generated font.

Text of Matthew 5:4 reads:
Blessed are they that mourn: 
for they shall be comforted.

title: Spencerian Calligraphy Capitals Practice Sheets | Ornamental Penmanship | Trace Template | Lettering | Pointed Pen | Script | Calligrapher
description:
Thank you for watching the video. Videography credit to my daughter Lucy (then 9 years old). The lettering "We are the ones..." ("we are the ones we've been waiting for") is the last line in June Jordan's Poem for South African Women.

Description: 
Step up your calligraphy practice considerably with this stroke by stroke 2-page guide for the elegant Spencerian Calligraphy style. Spencerian is considered to be the 1st American calligraphic hand, developed in the mid-19th century by P.R. Spencer. 

Digital download includes a total of 3 files:
- 17 pages of Spencerian capitals practice sheets plus 3 blank guideline sheets.
- 1 page of capitals with directional arrows of which way the strokes are lettered.
- 1 page of lower case letters with directional arrows of which way the strokes are lettered.

***Please note this is a digital product to be downloaded and printed. After you place the order you will be taken to the download page, and an email will be sent to you with your download link***

Files Included:

Print ready instant download digital file:
- Grayscale
- PDF and JPG format
- size 8.5" x 11"


Many thanks for your purchase and best wishes on your calligraphic journey!


TERMS OF USE: For personal use ONLY. These images may not be reproduced for resale or to give out in workshops.

title: Calligraphy Font, Script Font, Modern Calligraphy, Wedding Font, Font with swashes, Roselyn Font
description:
Wedding calligraphy font with swashes - Roselyn Script Font.

Roselyn Script is very elegant modern calligraphy font that will look awesome on logos, branding materials, wedding and event stationery, social media overlays, cards and so on. 

Roselyn includes Uppercase and Lowercase standard Characters, Numbers and Punctuation. Also the font contains alternate sets of Uppercase and Lowercase letters, Standard and Discretionary ligatures and Stylistic Alternates (for initial and final letters) to perfectly re-create natural calligraphy.

You can access all alternate letters and ligatures via Glyphs panel in your Software or for those whose software doesn't support it, please install the next files:

- Roselyn Alt.otf (alternate lowercase and uppercase letters)
- Roselyn Starting.otf (lowercase letters with beginning swashes)
- Roselyn Ending.otf (lowercase letters with ending swashes)

In order to use alternate letters, you need a program that supports OpenType Features (OTF) such as Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Indesign and Corel Draw. To open Glyphs panel in Photoshop, please, follow: Window - Glyphs; in Illustrator - Window - Types - Glyphs.

Also you can access the alternate glyph via Font Book (Mac user) or Windows Character Map (Windows user). Clear instruction is included in zip file.

You’ll get in zip file:

- Roselyn (OTF, TTF)
- Standard License Agreement (PDF)
- How to use get access to OTF (alternates and ligatures) (PDF)
- Additional swash files (for those, who don't have Glyphs panel): Roselyn Alt, Roselyn Starting, Roselyn Ending.

— TERMS OF USE —

What you CAN do:

- Personal and Commercial use (Unlimited projects & Unlimited sales).

What you CANNOT do:

- Sell or distribute the original font file;
- Use font on Print-on-Demand services unless you buy the Extended License;
- Digitize font and sell it as an embroidery font in your store;
- Claim my font as your own

More information about Standard License you can find in my shop Privacy policy (it's also included in zip).

Thanks so much for checking out my shop!

~ Oksana

See the last pictures. The frames have a beautiful look and are ideal for posters. Frame A4 (22 cm wide), A3 (31 cm wide) and A3+ (34 cm wide).

The frame for A5 is for installation. See the picture in the gallery.

How does the ordering process work?

1. Choose your style: Would you like to have a digital file for self-printing, a printed poster or the complete package poster and frame?
2. Choose your format: What size would you like? If you want a different size, just contact us.
3. Please tell us in the personalization box the name(s), your date, and/or a dedication.If no personalization, then simply enter "none".
4. Then send us your picture to lisya.store [!at] gmx.de or via WhatsApp to 0176 82588271 stating your order number. Please make sure that your image is high resolution, the pair is large on it and well exposed. Avoid blurry images, screenshot images, images on which the pair can only be seen very small. If you have several pictures to choose from, you are welcome to send them to us, and we will choose the most suitable one.

After receipt of order we start our work, as soon as we are finished you will receive a print preview and have the opportunity to suggest changes.


FAQ

♡ Can other objects or animals also be illustrated?
Yes, there is absolutely no limit. Everything is illustrated by us.

♡ Can several people be portrayed on a poster?
Yes, you can. Basically, photo editing is included in the prices, regardless of how many people are in the photo. If you have another photo, we can also implement it for an extra charge of 5 €. However, the payment processing of the other photos does not take place on Etsy. Just write to us.

♡ Can I choose the watercolor color and the background color?
Of course, you can tell us how you imagine it. If there are no wishes here, we adjust the colors.

♡ Our pet has died, is it possible to incorporate further wishes e.B. a halo or the dates of birth and death?
Yes, we are happy to do this free of charge. Just come to us.

♡ Is it possible to issue a voucher for a poster?
You want to make someone happy, but don't have a good picture? No problem, just give away a value voucher. Please contact us.

♡ When is the picture ready?
As a rule, we need up to 24 hours for your first preview and another day for quality inspection, format adjustment, and printing. Your poster is usually ready for dispatch after 2-3 working days.

Thank you for visiting our shop, Have fun browsing

Gold, Silver and Copper coated Shiny Metal options are produced with brushing and electropolishing method. Surface protection is also applied. The conventional painting process has not applied to the golden, copper and silver shiny options standard paint would not provide a shiny effect. 

The black, golden and copper painted versions are painted with powder paint a durable matte finish for long years. The painted versions are not shiny. You can take a look at our metal products for better understanding the difference between a coated/shiny and painted product.

Options for Painted Ones : Gold Painted, Silver Painted, Copper Painted and Black Painted.

90x90 cm  (36x36 inches)

•         This product will be sent as ready.

•         You can hang each product with a single nail from the hanging attachment on the back.

*Due to the nature of the metal, the varnish, and the handmade process in which the décor is being polished through a chemical procedure, the shiny décors are not impeccable. However, this does not affect the overall fine appearance of the artwork.*

Meaning of Ayatul Kursi (Surah Al-Baqara 2:255):
"Allah! There is no god but He - the Living, The Self-subsisting, Eternal. No slumber can seize Him Nor Sleep. His are all things In the heavens and on earth. ✔SUBLIMATION TRANSFER NEED TO KNOW:
* These transfers will not print white ink. If there is white in the design it will become the color of the fabric your apply it to.
* Each transfer has a ONE time use.
* Image color may very slightly due to screen solution
* Transfer must be used on a substrate coated for sublimation (mugs, tumblers, glass etc.)
* Sublimation prints should be used on at least a 50% polyester count garment that is white or light colored. The closer to 100% polyester you get, the brighter the image. The closer to 50% polyester you get, the more vintage the image.
* Sublimation will NOT work on cotton or dark colored shirts
* You MUST apply sublimation transfer with a heat press. They can not be applied with an iron or a Cricut Easy Press.

Vinyl decals can be applied to any smooth surface, such as:

title: Mental Health Awareness Sublimation Transfer, Ready to Press, Sublimation Transfer, Ready to Press Transfer, NOT DIGITAL
description:
NOT A DIGITAL DOWNLOAD

READY TO PRESS Sublimation Transfer Only

FREE SHIPPING WITH OVER $35 PURCHASE
*Shipped with tracking in hard rigid mailer and polymailer for protection*

Print Size:
*Mug- 3" on longest side
*Large Mug- 4" on longest side
*Infant/Toddler- 5.5" on longest side
*Youth- 7" on longest side
*Adult- 8-10" on longest side

APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS:
* Sublimation prints should be used on at least a 50% polyester count garment that is white or light colored.
*The closer to 100% polyester you get, the brighter the image.
*The closer to 50% polyester you get, the more vintage the image.
* Sublimation will NOT work on cotton or dark colored shirts.
* You MUST apply sublimation transfer with a heat press. It can not be applied with an iron.
* Press image at 400 degrees for 60 seconds.

OTHER TRANSFER OPTIONS: (Tumblers/Mugs)
Convection Oven
-385-400 Degrees 
-Tape around design with heat tape
-Heat for 6 minutes, turn halfway at 3 minute mark

Mug Press
-385-400 Degrees 
-Tape around design with heat tape
-Heat for 4 minutes

**TUMBLERS/MUGS must be sublimation tumblers. Sublimation tumblers have a polyester coating for the ink transfer to work.**

WHAT IS SUBLIMATION?

*Sublimation ink, when heated, turns into a gas that actually embeds itself into anything with a polyester coating. 

*This creates a cleaner, more professional look while allowing for a much more detailed image than what heat transfer vinyl can offer. Shading, gradients and a rainbow of colors are huge benefits to using sublimation transfers. 

*Sublimation must be used with at least 50% polyester (white or light colored garment) but will show better results the closer to 100% polyester your garment is (white or light colored garment). The higher the polyester content, the brighter and clearer your image will be. The lower the polyester content, the more vintage, faded or aged your image will be. Also, with a lower polyester content, you may see your image fade slightly with the first wash.

**TUMBLERS/MUGS must be sublimation tumblers. Sublimation tumblers have a polyester coating for the ink transfer to work.**

WHAT IS SUBLIMATION?

*Sublimation ink, when heated, turns into a gas that actually embeds itself into anything with a polyester coating. 

*This creates a cleaner, more professional look while allowing for a much more detailed image than what heat transfer vinyl can offer. Shading, gradients and a rainbow of colors are huge benefits to using sublimation transfers. 

*Sublimation must be used with at least 50% polyester (white or light colored garment) but will show better results the closer to 100% polyester your garment is (white or light colored garment). The higher the polyester content, the brighter and clearer your image will be. The lower the polyester content, the more vintage, faded or aged your image will be. Also, with a lower polyester content, you may see your image fade slightly with the first wash.

title: Beach lover SVG design, beach svg, vacation, summer fun, salty beach, sublimation download, shore vacation svg, PNG
description:
5 file formats included in 1 zip file
SVG PNG DXF EPS JPG

SVG is 12x12 and scalable to whatever size suits your needs
PNG is 15x15 in. 4500x4500 px - 300 DPI Transparent Background

File format information
SVG files are compatible with most die cut machines, such as Silhouette Cameo, Cricut, ScanNCut, etc…SVG is Scalable Vector Graphic and can be scaled without losing quality. You can also ungroup and change the color.

DXF files can be used in Silhouette Studio if you’ve not purchased the software upgrade to open SVG files. DXF files can also be used in most of the common laser software programs.

EPS Files can be used in software such as Affinity Designer, Adobe Photoshop and Illustrator.

PNG files can be printed with an inkjet printer or sublimation printer- my PNG files are created with a transparent background and are large enough in size to meet many printing needs.

JPG files are also printable files, however they do have a white background.

Please message me for any questions or concerns regarding my files.

My product preview images are created using mockups to showcase an idea or two of what the design can be used for. Preview images are low resolution. Your purchased files will be high quality/ high resolution and will not be watermarked.

Thank you for stopping by my shop, I hope you will find something you love. 


Happy crafting!

©Donkey Creek Designs

title: Personalized Acrylic Name Bookmark | Custom Hand-Lettered Bookmark | Book Lover Gift
description:
Beautifully hand lettered custom acrylic bookmark to keep track of the page you left on. 

PRODUCT INFORMATION
-Material: Acrylic
-Size: 2 X 6 inches
-Standard Ink: White (weather, smudge, and UV resistant)

CUSTOMIZATION
-Ink Color: The standard ink color is white, but black, gold, silver and rose gold inks are also available. Please indicate ink color in the personalization section.
-Background Color: There are over a dozen background colors available. In the personalization section, please indicate what color you would like the background painted or if you would like it to be left clear. In the customization section you may also indicate if you would like the entire background painted or if you would just like a simple paint swipe, leaving some of the clear acrylic exposed. If no preference is indicated then the default is to paint the entire bookmark background. See product photos for background color options.
-Ribbon Color: There are over a dozen ribbon colors available. In the customization section, please indicate what color you would like the ribbon to be. If no color is indicated then the standard white ribbon will be included in your order. See product photos for ribbon color options. 
-Personalization/Customization: Please indicate exact wording and/or name that you would like included on the bookmark. Adding extra wording details such as date, location, names, or hashtags are available. There will be an additional $2.00 charge. See the “How to Order” section for more information. 

HOW TO ORDER:
Select ink color, either ‘white’, ‘gold’, ‘black’, or ‘silver’.
Select the background color choice. (See product photos for background options)
In the customization box please specify what customizations you want by listing EXACT WORDING for the bookmark, ribbon color choice, AND if you would like the entire background painted or just a paint swipe of background color. 
If you are choosing to personalize further, please send me a direct Etsy message with your order number in the subject line. Then write a detailed message with information about what details you’d like added (such as wording, flowers, icons, etc.).

IMPORTANT NOTES:
-Making Changes to Orders: If you change your mind or notice something that needs to be changed with your sign please contact me immediately. I will do my best to accommodate the change, but I cannot guarantee any changes once the order has been placed.
-Damage: A layer of sealant will be applied to each sign once it is complete before shipping. The sealant helps to prevent damage such as chipping, smudging, UV rays and water. However, the signs are still at risk for damage. To avoid damage between the ship date and your event date I have placed a film or plastic layer on top of the sign. Please keep film on until event date to prevent any damage. 

PRODUCTION:
-Bookmarks are made to order and fully custom.
-Production takes 3-5 days before shipping. 
-If you are interested in a rush order, please send a direct message as soon as possible with the desired ship date. A rush fee will be applied to order. The fee will vary depending on the sign’s size and details.

RETURNS AND CANCELLATIONS:
Because each chalkboard item is custom and made to order, there are no returns or cancellations. If the item received is not to your liking or damaged please contact me within 14 days of delivery via direct Etsy message with a photo of the sign, order number, and detailed message. By purchasing this item, you are agreeing to this return and cancellation policy.

title: Wedding vinyl. Wedding iron on vinyl. Wedding transfers. Bride. Bridesmaid. Groom. Best man and more. Bridal iron on stickers.
description:
Decorate your bridal robes, bags, t-shirts, many kinds of textiles with this heat transfer ( HTV ) iron vinyl decal.

Please choose your colour and bridal role from the drop-down menu and leave the name you require in the personalisation section,

The transfer comes with a name and a bridal role. 

They are 20 x 10 for single roles such as bride, bridesmaid, flower girl, roles on one line. 
They are 23 x 15 centimeters for double roles such as mother of the bride or groom, maid of honour on 2 lines.


* If the role you require is not listed please leave the role in the personalisation section or the notes at checkout. 

Easy to apply with a household iron in 10-15 seconds. 

* Preheat the iron on the highest cotton setting (ideally 165C) WITH THE STEAM TURNED OFF! 
* Iron the garment to remove any creases and moisture 
* Place the garment on a hard surface
* Remove the transfer and the thick plastic carrier sheet from the thin plastic protective sheet
* Place the transfer sheet with decoration on top of the garment
* Cover with a thin piece of cloth or baking paper for best results
 * Place the iron on the transfer and hold in place for 10-15 seconds, applying  lots of even pressure (do not move the iron ) 
* Whilst hot, remove the cloth or baking paper, peel back the plastic carrier sheet, leaving the vinyl transfers on the clothing. 
If the design has not adhered perfectly, repeat the previous steps.

* Wash the garment with your new transfer on inside out on a 30 degree wash, with no fabric condition, leave to air dry. 
 
Full instructions on how to apply your transfer will be added to your order. 

The transfer comes with a name and a bridal role. 

If you prefer just a role please leave the personalisation section blank.

title: SUBLIMATION TRANSFER, Straight Outta Patience  transfer, #momlife transfer, t-shirt transfer, transfer only, ready to press
description:
THIS IS A PHYSICAL SUBLIMATION TRANSFER. IT IS NOT A DIGITAL IMAGE

This sublimation transfer is meant to go on shirts, pillow cases, bags, blankets, mugs, tumblers, etc. Please make sure the item you are putting it on is meant for sublimation. And make sure you measure your item to make sure you order the right size transfer.

These transfers are ready to press. They must be applied using a heat press to make sure you get good and even pressure. An iron or easy press is not recommended. The heat press needs to be 385-400 degrees and under medium pressure for 60 seconds.

Sublimation dye adheres best to polyester items. If you are using a shirt you want to have at least 50% poly which can give a more faded vintage look. To get more vibrant colors you want to use 100% poly.

You will want to use items that are white or a light color. The image is dyed into the material so if you use a darker color you will not see the image, but you can do a bleached design on a shirt to be able to see the image and using heather colors are best. These transfers do not print white so anywhere on the image that is white will not show up and it will be whatever color the shirt is.

Since the image is dyed into the shirt you cannot feel the image. It is not vinyl so it will never crack or peel off. This will be a permanent design.

The colors may vary on the screen compared to in person. The image might look dull on the transfer but will be vibrant once you use the heat press and put it on the item.

All measurements are an estimate and will be sized accordingly to the image. All transfers will be printed without my watermark design.

I am not responsible For late/Lost/damaged packages. If you would like insurance to cover those items place purchase using Priority mail. once I drop off at post office shipping is out of my hands.

If you want to discuss a custom design please message my etsy shop and we can go over details. There are no returns on sublimation transfers.

description:

Sketch: pink
The Dilly: copper orange
The Ritz: gold
Fortnum & Mason: mint green
Aqua Shard: pale blue
Dorchester: lilac purple
One Aldwych: chocolate brown
Berkeley: cream

The lid of the tin includes a printed swatch card if requested.  

Paint pans come with magnets attached to the bottom to help them stay in the tin. 

Our homemade binder is made with the highest quality gum arabic available. We do not use honey or any other animal products in our paints, so they are vegan-friendly.

Every paint is handmade with love, which means you may notice some air bubbles, bumps, or cracks. This is completely normal and does not affect the quality of the paint. Every quarter pan is filled 3 times to ensure you get the most paint possible, though air bubbles do occasionally occur.

Not intended for use on skin. Please do not ingest.

For best results, apply 1 to 2 drops of water to the paint and wait a minute, then reactivate the paint with a paint brush.

INTERNATIONAL SHIPPING NOTE: I am currently shipping from London, England. I offer affordable international shipping because I want to share my paint with everyone. title: Printable Cursive handwriting worksheets | Printable handwriting worksheets | 41 Pages for cursive handwriting practice | size- A4 PDF & PNG
description:
Note: This worksheet set is only for digital downloads. This set is available as an "instant download" and due to this, not eligible for a refund. You can message me with your questions prior to the order.

These are ready to print Cursive Handwriting practice worksheets(size A4). These cursive handwriting worksheets are very useful for all age group (Especially useful for kids(preschool and toddlers) and students who want to learn and to improve their print handwriting)

This package contains 6 different PDFs and PNGs of cursive handwriting sheets(41 Pages) in one zip file.

PDF-1 SHAPES AND STROKES PRACTICES(2 pages)
This worksheet contains a set of different essential shapes and strokes practice. These practices will help to enhance hand muscle movements. The hand muscle movements are very essential things to write any letter very easily and neatly. Also, each letter or alphabet is made up of one or a combination of different shapes. So this practice worksheet will help you to draw the letters or alphabets in perfects shapes. This will improve your letter formation. 

PDF-2: UPPERCASE CURSIVE LETTERS (ALPHABETS) PRACTICES (4 Pages)
This contains the practice sheets for cursive uppercase letters. You simply trace and write the letters on your own. Practice writing these letters slowly but accurately. 

PDF-3: LOWERCASE CURSIVE LETTERS (ALPHABETS) PRACTICES (4 Pages)
This contains the practice sheets for cursive lowercase letters. You simply trace and write the letters on your own. Practice writing these cursive letters slowly but accurately. 

PDF-4: WORDS WRITING PRACTICES (5 Pages)
This contains daily used words such as names of days and months, names of animals, names of colors, names of fruits, etc. Trace the word and write the same word in the empty space provided. Try to maintain proper forms of the letters.

PDF-5: SEPARATE PRACTICE FOR EACH UPPER AND LOWERCASE LETTER(26 Pages)
This contains 26 practice pages. Each page contains each capital and small letter. 

PDF-6: BLANK TEMPLATE(BLANK PRACTICE SHEET) (4 pages)
This contains one empty template sheet that you can use for your own practice.

Practice daily for at least 30 min to 1 Hrs. First start with shapes and strokes practice. These shape and stroke practices are very important as they help to improve hand movement and muscle memory. Then you start writing individual letters. Observe the formation of each letter properly. Observe properly how the letters are formed with the help of different shapes, that will help you to write that letter easily. Write letters slowly but accurately. Once you improve your formation of letters then you can write then with ease. Do the same thing for cursive upper and lowercase letters. Give yourself the proper time for practice. Monitor your improvements every week. 

These sheets are created on A4 size paper. You can simply take print outs on A4 size paper(SCALE FIT TO PAPER) and start practicing. For any queries, you can mail us on makworldchannel@gmail.com . You can also give your valuable feedback on the comment and review section.

NOTE:
THESE ARE THE COPIES OF WORKSHEETS IN MY OWN HANDWRITING ON A4 PAPER. THESE ARE FOR PERSONAL USE ONLY, DON NOT SHARE WITH ANYONE. DO NOT REUPLOAD OR SHARE ON ANY DIGITAL PLATFORM. THANK YOU.

title: Custom T-shirt and Hoodie Designs - Iron on Shirt Designs - Multi-Color, Printed DIY Iron on
description:
Don't let that plain shirt dull your wardrobe out! With these personalized transfers, you can put almost anything on that t-shirt, hoodie, hat, or anything with a cotton or polyester blend. We've been printing heat transfers for custom apparel shops for a while and realized that it's not often that people want to order 10-20 of the same design and we have a solution for just that! 

These heat transfers are made of high quality HTV made by Siser and come with transfer film applied. All you'll need to do is turn on that heat press or iron and get ready to transform that shirt! These transfers will work with any combination of cotton or polyester. We do not suggest using it on other fabrics, however, you're free to try it on anything you'd like. 

This is not a simple sticker, however, it's easy to apply even with a standard iron and it's no where near similar to the stuff you'll find with an inkjet printer. This material has been commonly seen to outlast the shirts themselves with proper application. 

We require 2-3 days processing time after the artwork is supplied. We suggest using vector art that you have permission to use. (Sorry, no copyright material!)  We can print any photos or artwork that you have, however, please keep in mind that we cannot guarantee the resolution as scaling the images to fit the 10-12 inch transfer can decrease the quality. 

- To note, the size options are for the largest dimension. For example, you would want to choose the 12" option for a design that is 10x12 inches. Please reach out if you have any questions.  

------------------------------------------

FAQ's: 
Please review this video for information on transfers and other FAQs: https://youtu.be/M2ZKYTjXhJ8

1. What kind of artwork or file type should I use? 
      - Etsy only supports .jpg or .png, however, we prefer lossless formats (vector) such as .ai, .eps, .pdf, .svg

2. Can you remove the background of my image? 
      - In most cases, no. If your image is low resolution we will likely not be able to remove the background. If the image has a transparent background, the background will be white. This does not apply to most vector files and in some cases, we can remove backgrounds. Please message us if you'd like us to review your artwork. 

3. Do you require a bleed for printing? 
      - Yes, if the design does not have a 1/4" bleed, we will add a small white outline to the overall design. In some cases, we can match the background color or if the image already has an outline, we can match that color. 

4. How do I install the transfer? 
      - The decal is sandwiched between two films. First, remove the back film which should not be sticky and should have a frosted/foggy appearance to it. Then, place the decal with top film still installed onto your garment. Press the decal on the garment for 10 seconds at 310 degrees and then peel the top film off while the shirt is still warm. While peeling the sticky top film away from the garment, make sure you watch for any edges of the decal that peel up with it. If they do peel up, try pressing it again for 7 seconds. Always wash the garment inside out with cold water only and on a gentle cycle.  

5. How do I iron on my decal? 
      - We recommend using a heat press but irons can do the trick. Please take a look at the end of this video which goes through the install process: https://youtu.be/M2ZKYTjXhJ8

6. Can I return my transfer? 
      - We do not offer returns or refunds on custom orders such as HTV transfers

7. My image/decal doesn't look good (fuzzy, pixelated, etc)
       -  We are not responsible or liable for graphics that are supplied in low resolution
       -  Make sure you supply us with the best quality image you have as we cannot make an image look better

8. Can I get a proof of my design? 
      -  We will supply a proof only if requested and only if an order has been submitted
      - If you are not happy with the proof, we can make 1 revision or refund a portion of the order less compensation for graphic design labor.

9. My question is not listed. 
      - Please reach out to us with any question you have prior to ordering.

10. I've placed an order but do not like the artwork/proof
      - We understand that after making a purchase, you may like to cancel. If we haven't started processing the order (sent proofs, begun design, or started production) we will consider refunds on a case by case basis. Please note that if we have created a proof or done any design work, partial refunds may be provided. 

11. Do you offer gang printing? 
     - We do offer bulk printing at a discounted rate, however, the prices listed here are for single image prints. Please contact us for more information or for bulk print quotes.

12. Can you print smaller than 10 inches?  
     - Absolutely! We can print most any sizes but due to material costs, our minimum charge is a 10" design. So if you need a design printed 6" wide, select the 10" option and specify the correct size via an order note or by messaging us.
personalization_instructions: Please message us the design you would like to use and add any additional details here. You can also email it to chris@vaporsigns.com (ai,eps,svg,png,jpg,pdf)

title: Baby Footprint + Birth Date + Handwritten Chinese Calligraphy 知足常乐 True happiness lies within you (Baby Gift/13in x 13in/Wall Art)
description:
Baby Footprint + Birth Date + Handwritten Chinese Calligraphy 知足常乐 True happiness lies in contentment (Baby Gift/13in x 13in/Wall Art)

知足常乐 means ”Happiness lies within you" or “Happiness lies in contentment". It came from ancient Chinese philosopher Laozi 老子. The character 足 means enough, 知足means contentment. 足also happens to mean feet in Chinese, therefore sometimes people insert their babies' footprints to replace the character in calligraphy as decorations and express their best wishes for the newborns.

This item is a tasteful house decoration and a perfect gift for newborns. 

This item includes:
1.  A pre-mounted soft card with raw Xuan paper
2. Handwritten Chinese calligraphy
3. A washable Non-Toxic Ink Stamp Pad for Baby Footprint
4. A 13x13 black frame with a matte finish

INSTRUCTIONS:

HOW TO INSTALL THE FONT ON PC OR MAC:

Unzip your font folder and double click on the font to install it.

*For Ipad and iPhone users, you can search on the "app store" some free "font manager" app, it is 100% compatible on IPad and iPhone as well.


///


CRICUT AND SILHOUETTE:

Please note. I do not offer support for Cricut, however, I provide you with some instructions bellow that might help you.

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON PC:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF). Double-click it!
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.
Congratulations! Your font is now installed.
Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE ON MAC OS X:

1.
Unzip your font folder.

2.
Locate the font file inside the font folder. Your font file will be either an OpenType Format (OTF) or a TrueType format (TTF).
Once you double-click the font file, an installation window appears. Just click Install.

Congratulations! Your font is now installed.

Now, the trick to using it in Cricut Design Space is to be sure you RELOAD Design Space before you try to find the font. That usually means just clicking the refresh icon in your browser.

Once Cricut Design Space is reloaded, click the Text icon, type some text, click the Fonts menu, make sure the word “All” is highlighted, and type in the first few letters of the new font you uploaded — when your font appears, click it to apply it to your text!

And that’s it!

HOW TO UPLOAD FONTS TO CRICUT DESIGN SPACE IN IOS 11 OR HIGHER ON AN IPAD OR IPHONE:

First, go to the app store and get a free app called iFont. Once you’re in the app store, click on the Search button down at the bottom and type in iFont. Click on the download icon. After the app finishes downloading, click to open iFont.

Download the font to your iPad or iPhone.

iFont should open with the Open Zip Archive screen. You should then be directed back to iFont. On the left, you’ll see an option to Install the Maker Penwriting Regular font. Tap the Install button. You’ll be guided through a series of menus. Tap Allow. Settings should open showing a window to Install Profile. Tap Install. You may be prompted for your device’s passcode. You may have to tap install a couple more times to complete the process. You should see a screen that says Profile Installed. Tap Done. The font is now installed on your device.

Restart the Cricut Design Space app. Click on the text at the bottom. Click on the All tab because of the app defaults to the Cricut tab. Type in the name of the font you just installed. Tap on it. You should now be back at the Canvas screen. Type in text to see what it looks like.


///


HOW TO MANUALLY INSTALL FONTS FOR SILHOUETTE:


Note: You do not need to download the font into the Silhouette software. Once the Mia font is installed on your computer in your font directory, the font will show up as an available option for cutting letters once the Silhouette software is opened.


INSTALL THE FONT ON A PC:

1. After you purchase the font, your font will be available to download. Right-click on the font link from Etsy and "Save link as" to your computer. A zipped folder will be downloaded to your default download location on your computer. It will be named "Mia Font Commercial.zip" on your PC:

Depending on your download environment, the download may show in the downloads section of your browser OR in the default download location

Open the downloaded folder

2. Double-click on "Mia Font Commercial.zip" folder to install (A font management window will open)

3. Select the Install option in the upper-left of the window

4. The Install button will turn grey, indicating that the font has been installed


INSTALL THE FONT ON A MAC:

1. After you purchase the font, a zipped folder will be available and downloaded to your default download location on your computer. It will be named "Mia Font Commercial.zip" on your PC:

Depending on your download environment, the download may show in the downloads section of your browser OR in the default download location

Open the downloaded folder

2. Double-click on "Mia Font Commercial.zip" folder to install (A font management window will open)

3. Select the Install option in the lower-right of the window

4. The font management window will close, indicating that the font has been installed

Voila! :)

♥♥♥ PRODUCT DETAILS♥♥♥

***PLEASE READ BEFORE ORDERING:  This listing is for LABELS ONLY, tubes ARE NOT included*** 

- Available in clear (transparent) premium glossy sticker.  Size of each label: 1.75” x 0.75".

- Printed with REAL FOIL or black ink.  Foil colors are: Gold, Rose gold, Silver, Iridescent, white, Light Pink, Hot Pink, Teal, Mint, Blue, Green and Red. 

Our stickers come in sheets, price shown in this listing is for 1 sheet of 48 stickers. If you want more than 1 sheet (48 stickers) please change the quantity on the dropdown menu.
  
These stickers are printed with REAL FOIL in our studio. They are really good quality, but please note since this is real foil it is subject to little imperfections in some occasions.   

One digital proof is included upon request. We will wait 5 days for a proof confirmation. If we do not receive approval once those 5 days have passed, we will ship your order as shown on the proof.

For our foil labels for weddings and other events go to
https://www.etsy.com/shop/InkYourStyle?ref=listing-shop-header-item-count&section_id=23728654

For our return address labels go to
https://www.etsy.com/shop/InkYourStyle?ref=condensed_trust_header_title_reviews&section_id=23854311

We also have GIFT TAGS, to see all our gift tags designs you can go to

https://www.etsy.com/shop/InkYourStyle?ref=listing-shop-header-item-count&section_id=24714956
 
♥♥♥ HOW TO APPLY♥♥♥
Recommendations for applying the labels with optimal adhesion: 

- Clean your hands and the destination surface. Any debris, dust, moisture, or natural oils can interfere with the adhesive, weakening the bond.  If bubble solution has spilled and dried on the tubes and the tubes are not cleaned, the stickers won't stick or they will start to pill off right after applying them.

- Apply the center of the label first and then work out toward the edges. This reduces some of the tension on the ends of the label which will help it stay down.

- Use pressure when sticking the labels to your surface. Our products are pressure-sensitive, so more pressure equates to a stronger bond.

description:
These lovely Vow booklets are Letterpress printed in antique blue ink on a pillowy white handmade paper. Each booklet is finished with a silk-like ribbon. Booklets come as a His & Hers pair. Inside are 6 pages, giving couples plenty of room to write their wedding vows. These are perfect for your 'something blue' and make a great gift for newly engaged couples, wedding shower gifts, or bridal shower gifts. 

These Vow booklets were printed on my vintage 1887 Letterpress printer who is affectionately nicknamed Cleveland. Yes, Cleveland is over 100 years old and runs smooth as butter! Letterpress has an organic personal touch that you can literally feel on the paper. With original artwork each booklet printed is run through my hands and examined while being printed. And in a world where everything is generic and mass produced, when you receive something that was made by hand it stands out! 


Size of each Booklet- 4.25 x 5.5in

description:
This is handmade mineral watercolor in half-pan size.

The color is brushed copper.

The watercolor was made in a small batch with a use of natural and organic materials. The pigment is a powdered non-toxic mineral and the binding is a combination of organic gum arabic, organic honey, organic essential oil (preservative), and vegetable glycerin. There are no other additives or fillers, just pure pigment. It is safe for children.

This watercolor is highly saturated and a small quantity would be enough to embellish your artwork or calligraphy. This means that it will last long!

Make your own holiday cards or thank you cards or add an oomph to store-bought postcards or your artistic business cards. Use these watercolors in coloring books or in your lettering practice.

This sparkly watercolor is easy to layer for opaque coverage or blend with other watercolors or ink. You can use it for drawing or calligraphy and lettering. It looks bright and is quite visible on different tones of paper (see images with examples).
